review_text: Sering banget belanja di sini, hampir tiap pekan. Selalu suka karena sayurannya itu seger seger banget. Di sini btuh ada Non-halal station juga, jadi buat yg muslim hati-hati ya salah masuk ke area non halal (mereka terpisah gitu sih). review_translated_text: I shop here very often, almost every week. Always like it because the vegetables are really fresh. In terms of price, its a bit more expensive than traditional markets, but its okay, the vegetables are fresh, hahaha. There needs to be a non-halal station here too, so for Muslims, be careful if you enter the wrong non-halal area (they are separated like that). Then payments here can also be cashless using QRIS, apart from cash, of course. The sea fish is also fresh.

review_text: Pasar Modern BSD City, located in South Tangerang, Indonesia, offers a vibrant shopping experience that blends traditional market vibes with modern conveniences. This marketplace is particularly noted for its wide range of products, including fresh produce, local delicacies, and international foods, groceries, fruit, fish, halal and haram meat, providing a unique shopping experience for visitors. The markets lively atmosphere and modern facilities complete with variety of goods, snack and food sold in the small stalls scattered throughout this market. Its a great place to find everything from daily necessities to specialty items. However, detailed information about opening hours or any entrance access and parking isnt readily available, so it might be wise to check ahead before planning a visit. Parking in the market complex is sometime limited; if it is full, we can use paid street parking on the side of the road along the perimeter of complex.

review_text: Service was ok, been here around a dozen times if I can recall it right. Seating is a bit tricky since its always packed. Food is decent but comparing the food and the price could be difficult, its debatable but for me personally not great, it can be lowered a bit. I kinda forgot about wheelchair access, which may exist but space from table to table is too tight for wheelchair imho. Food usually ordered: potato gratin, fish and chips, Caesars salad for all these 3, theyre not a punchy dish but nothing to complain about, the gratin could be a bit salty with a pinch of other seasoning to heighten each variance difference. Funny enough, its called Bsteak Grill and pancake but I never order the steak nor remember whether they  exist on the menu, maybe the price turned me off? Oh well Im typically just chasing price balanced food and maybe they failed to convince me on this. Waiters...gosh the whole squad are there but calling one to serve you when youre on the table, especially outdoors is not an easy one. The waiter dropped a whole glass of drinks on me in the past and compensation was given. Throughout my visits, I think 50% of those I heard a shattering sound of glasses or else. Parking is not difficult but not easy if youre looking for a slot just near the entrance. Would I recommend this one? Nope, so why am I here often? Either Friends pay my dinner here or events.

review_text: Atmosphere: Resto yang nyaman buat hangout dengan teman maupun keluarga. Staff: Dari receiptionist di bawah tangga sampai di atas semua staffnya ramah dan servicesnya    . Penjelasan ttg sauce dan menu juga ramah dan jelas. Terutama mba Welly yg manis ramah dan helpful banget. Untuk makanannya : Full Rack Ribs: juicy, tender dan rasanya cocok, smokeynya berasa. Pulled pork Sandwich : juicy, wellblended semua. Cocok di lidah kita. Pulled pork Fried Rice:  wangi smokey, tekstur nasi cocok utk nasgor dan rasanya juga cocok. Food Presentation: Semua wellplated. Sayang ga difoto tadi lsg pada makan. Overall semua cocok sama keluarga kita. Thanks you, sehat selalu n sukses untuk  resto, all staff dr receiptionist sd cheff
response_from_owner_text: Dear Ms. Hera, Thank you so much for your detailed and glowing review! Were delighted to hear that you found our restaurant to be a comfortable place for hanging out with friends and family. Our staff takes great pride in providing friendly and attentive service, from the receptionist to everyone else, and were thrilled that you appreciated their efforts. Its wonderful to know that our explanations about the sauces and menu were helpful and clear, especially thanks to our team member, Welly, who always goes above and beyond to assist our guests. Were thrilled that you enjoyed our Full Rack Ribs, Pulled Pork Sandwich, and Pulled Pork Fried Rice! It means a lot to us that you found them juicy, tender, and perfectly flavored, with just the right amount of smokiness. And were glad you appreciated the food presentation, even if you couldnt resist digging in before taking photos! Thank you again for your kind words and for choosing to dine with us. We wish you continued health and success, and we look forward to welcoming you and your family back to our restaurant soon. Warm regards, HotLicks
review_translated_text: Atmosphere: A comfortable restaurant for hanging out with friends and family. Staff: From the receiptionist at the bottom of the stairs to the top, all the staff are friendly and the service is     . Explanations about sauces and menus are also friendly and clear. Especially Ms. Welly, who is sweet, friendly and very helpful. For the food: Full Rack Ribs: juicy, tender and the taste is perfect, the smokey taste. Pulled pork sandwich: juicy, well blended everything. Suitable on our tongue. Pulled pork Fried Rice: smokey aroma, the texture of the rice is suitable for nasgor and the taste is also suitable. Food Presentation: All wellplated. Its a shame I didnt take a photo while eating. Overall everything suits our family. Thank you, always healthy and successful for the restaurant, all staff from receiptionist to cheff

Ini terakhir kalinya saya mengunjungi tempat ini. Sejak manajer terakhir dan banyak anggota staf mengundurkan diri, ini bukan pelayanan yang baik. Staf tidak terlatih dengan baik. Dan jika saya ingin membayar dengan uang tunai, itu bahkan tidak bisa. Kl tidak bisa jgn bayar, mereka Merujuk UU Mata Uang, segala pembayaran dalam bentuk uang rupiah wajib diterima oleh seluruh pelaku kegiatan usaha di Indonesia. Sebaiknya sistem pembayaran yang berlaku pada setiap kali transaksi terjadi adalah sistem pembayaran optional.
review_translated_text: This is the last time I visit this place. Since the last manager and many staff members resigned, this has not been good service. Staff not well trained. And if I want to pay with cash, its not even possible. If they cant, dont pay, they refer to the Currency Law, all payments in rupiah must be accepted by all business actors in Indonesia. It is recommended that the payment system that applies every time a transaction occurs is an optional payment system.

review_text: We were interested trying this place because of their great reviews on google and we went there for dinner. First impression : typical american family restaurant vibes , we ordered their brisket , porkribs , nachos , and their recomendation juicy lucy burger.. Brisket 2/10 : lack of seasoning , a bit dry Pork ribs 1/10 : the souce overpowering the meat , for 60rb / bones totally not worth it , you can find better pork ribs in another restaurant just across Hot Licks. Nachos : 5/10 : very lack of presentation , lack of seasoning on the meat Jucy lucy burger : 3/10 : the meat was cooked perfectly but sadly the sauce over power everything , for that kind of price you can get better burger at other restaurant. Overall we are very disappointed with this restaurant

Food: -corn bread jalapeno nya antik banget, makin di makan makin enak -brisket nya quality banget -smoke rib nya smokeeeyyy bngt sampe ke dlm2 daging nya -kita pesen rib eye nya, gak yg paling enak di jkt (bnyk yg lebih enak dengan harga yg sama or lebih mahal dikit) tp overall okay -acar timun nya authentic banget -yg paling CRAZY SAOS NYA !!!! (Semua enak! Ini gak ketemu tempat lain) Embience nya enak, dingin resto nya, penerangan cukup dan suasana asik Service nya ok banget! Sabar banget Ka Diana, bolak balik ke dapur masti in rib eye yg punya kita tingkat kematangan nya sesuai sama yg kita order. Dikasih bonus es cream pula Bakal balik lg sih
response_from_owner_text: Dear Ms. Kezia, Thank you for sharing your detailed feedback on your dining experience with us! Were thrilled to hear that you found our Jalapeno corn bread to be uniquely delicious and that the more you indulge, the better it gets. We appreciate your honesty regarding the rib eye, and well certainly take your feedback into consideration to ensure we continue to improve and meet your expectations. Its wonderful to know that you enjoyed our pickled cucumbers and found them to be authentic. And were ecstatic that you found our sauces to be crazy delicious! We pride ourselves on offering unique and flavorful sauces that elevate our dishes. Were glad that you enjoyed the ambiance of our restaurant, with its cool atmosphere, comfortable temperature, and adequate lighting. Were delighted to hear that you had an exceptional experience with our service! Kak Diana and our team take pride in providing attentive and patient service to ensure your satisfaction. Its fantastic to hear that your rib eye was cooked exactly to your preference and that you received a bonus of ice cream as a special treat. Thank you for your kind words and for choosing to dine with us. We look forward to welcoming you back again soon for another wonderful dining experience! Warm regards, HotLicks.
review_translated_text: Food: -The jalapeno corn bread is really vintage, the more you eat it, the better it gets -The brisket is really high quality -The smoked ribs are really smokey, right into the meat -We ordered the rib eye, its not the best in Jakarta (there are lots of better ones at the same price or a little more expensive) but overall its okay -The cucumber pickles are really authentic -the most CRAZY SAUCE!!!! (Everything is delicious! You cant find this anywhere else) The ambiance is good, the restaurant is cool, the lighting is sufficient and the atmosphere is cool The service is really good! Very patient, Ka Diana, going back and forth to the kitchen, the masti in rib eye that we had had the same level of doneness as what we ordered. Also given a bonus of ice cream Ill be back again

Untuk toilet harus keluar, ke arah belakang Cafe. Sedikit catatan, banyak colokan yang rumah nya rusak, colokan di lantai juga beberapa tidak berfungsi. Mungkin bisa jadi catatan untuk di maintenance atau diganti. Squid ink fried rice 9/10 Porsi cukup banyak, rasa nya enakk overall. I like it. Hanya lumayan lama, hampir 1/2 jam menunggu. Hot cappuccino 7/20 Parkir 8/10 Untuk parkir bisa di samping atau di basement. Cukup banyak spot untuk parkir.
review_translated_text: The location is at the Brooklyn Apartment, Alam Sutera. This is my first time visiting here, in the afternoon around PK 18.00. Service 9/10 The server is friendly, informative and the service is quite fast. Drinks came out approximately 5-7 minutes after ordering. The food took a while, around 20-25 minutes, when it arrived it was quite busy, there was a private room which was full, so I ordered there first. Place 9/10 There are choices of large tables, medium tables and small tables. Lots of plugs, on the walls and on the floor. The room is clean, a bit dark, but still okay. Good for WFC or for meetings. To use the toilet, you have to go outside, towards the back of the cafe. A little note, many of the plugs in the housing are damaged, some of the plugs on the floor also dont work. Maybe it could be a note for maintenance or replacement. Squid ink fried rice 9/10 The portion is quite large, the taste is good overall. I like it. Just quite a long time, almost 1/2 hour wait. Hot cappuccino 7/20 Parking 8/10 Parking can be on the side or in the basement. There are quite a lot of spots for parking.

Such a lovely laid back place to enjoy delicious food and good coffee (V60 coffee was better than the Americano). This is a spot I can spend hours reading a book and enjoying the treats available from the unique, creative menu. Today, I had the Deep Fried Ube Sticks with dragon fruit sauce and the Croque - Monsieur with Egg. The ube sticks are pleasant, not overly sweet, but not bland either. It has a enjoyable subtly sweet taste and nice texture that is more airy than its deep-fried name would suggest.  The dragon fruit sauce complements it very well and Im surprised more places do not offer either uelbe or dragon fruit sauce in their menu. The main event is the croque, however. Just tasty and well-balanced, but not heavy. Its a nice light meal thats a step above from similar breakfast sandwiches. The coffee is probably the least tantalizing, at least with the Americano, but the V60 hand-brewed coffee with Ethiopia-Sadiloya reserve beans made it up. Thats a good selection of beans.

Eazy Coffee sudah jelas cafe dengan konsep Specialty Coffee Shop terbaik di Jombang. Mereka menggunakan 100% Arabica coffee beans yang mengutamakan flavor serta aroma, not so much in  body  seperti cafe lain yang biasanya menggunakan campuran kopi Robusta dalam house blend-nya. Mesin La Marzocco Linea PB + Mythos 1 Grinder + Mazzer Kony Grinder yang digunakan Eazy Coffee di Bar mereka jelas jadi jaminan kualitas serta konsistensi coffee based drinks! Dengan kualitas yang ditawarkan sama (bahkan lebih) dengan Coffee Shop di Jakarta maupun kota besar lainnya, Eazy Coffee menawarkan harga jual produk yang value for money sekali! Well, we ll be back again surely..
review_translated_text: Eazy Coffee is clearly the cafe with the best Specialty Coffee Shop concept in Jombang. They use 100% Arabica coffee beans which prioritize flavor and aroma, not so much in the body like other cafes which usually use a mixture of Robusta coffee in their house blend. The La Marzocco Linea PB + Mythos 1 Grinder + Mazzer Kony Grinder machine that Eazy Coffee uses in their bar is clearly a guarantee of the quality and consistency of coffee based drinks! With the same quality offered (if not more) as Coffee Shops in Jakarta and other big cities, Eazy Coffee offers product selling prices that are truly value for money! Well, well be back again surely..

review_text: Tempat spesialis makan kari di Alsut. Yang menarik, karinya tanpa santan. Jadi rasanya beda sama kari biasa khas indonesia, tapi gak kayak kari jepang juga. Unik lah. Ke sini pesen yang spesial, ayamnya campuran 3 jenis : katsu, ayam asap dan ayam kecap. Paling enak menurutku ayam asapnya, sayangnya tidak disajikan dalam kondisi panas. Ada 2 varian yang ukuran small (47k) dan regular (52k), yang membedakan adalah ukuran nasinya ya. Bukan banyaknya lauknya. Dan kita bisa pesen tingkat pedesnya. Kita pesan level 2 dan masih sangat enteng banget tapi cukup memberi sensasi pedes2 dikit yang bikin mantap dan sesuai sama lidah orang Indo Bakso goreng dan gyoza nya juga just oke. Monggo dicoba buat ngerasain sensasi beda dari rasa makan kari
review_translated_text: A place that specializes in eating curry in Alsut. Whats interesting is that the curry is without coconut milk. So the taste is different from ordinary Indonesian curry, but not like Japanese curry either. Its unique. Here, order the special, the chicken is a mixture of 3 types: katsu, smoked chicken and soy sauce chicken. I think the smoked chicken is the best, unfortunately its not served hot. There are 2 variants, small (47k) and regular (52k), the difference is the size of the rice. Not the many side dishes. And we can order the spicy level. We ordered level 2 and it was still very light but just enough to give a slightly spicy sensation which made it delicious and suited the Indonesian tongue The fried meatballs and gyoza are also just okay. Please try it to feel a different sensation from the taste of eating curry

Picked this place to have lunch with my friend and apparently it wasnt bad at all. Pertama dateng karena vibes tempatnya dari luar keliatan sangat comfortable, juga karena  dari pilihan makanannya yg banyak dengan tipikal comfort food, plus beberapa kali liat review dari food blogger dan cek review google juga overall oke. Untuk main dishes nya sih enak dengan porsi yg cukup, but I guess some will say its overprice compared with the portion. Tapi untuk side dishesnya not to my liking sih: rasa dimsumnya too average, agak nanggung dan kalo ini jujur secara size dan presentasi kurang sesuai dengan harganya. Mungkin ketinggian ekspektasi juga sih karena liat review2 dan secara konsep ini kan Chinese Resto next level gitu. Tapi di luar itu dari sisi service, kebersihan tempat, ambience, dan kenyamanan udah oke banget. Maybe will come back again some times to try their other dishes, jujur dari menu dan pilihan makanan menarik banget soalnya.
review_translated_text: Picked this place to have lunch with my friend and apparently it wasnt bad at all. Firstly, I came because the vibes of the place from the outside looked very comfortable, also because of the large selection of food typical of comfort food, plus I saw several reviews from food bloggers and checked Google reviews and overall it was okay. As for the main dishes, they are delicious with sufficient portions, but I guess some will say its overpriced compared with the portion. But the side dishes are not to my liking: the taste of the dim sum is too average, a bit overbearing and if Im honest, the size and presentation dont match the price. Maybe expectations are also high because I saw the reviews and in concept this is a next level Chinese Resto. But apart from that, in terms of service, cleanliness of the place, ambience and comfort, its really good. Maybe will come back again some times to try their other dishes, honestly the menu and food choices are really interesting.

The food was okay but the service and cleanliness were horrible. Probably, I just caught them on the bad day. Next visit, I can see significant improvements.  Toilet was clean and smell good. Tables are properly cleaned. Staff had more smiles than ever. Lets talk about the food. I really enjoyed the big breakfast menu. Buranchi is definitely my fave western brunchy place to go. The eggs are cooked perfectly, with tasty bacon, sauteed mushroom and many other things. All items on the plate compliment each other in perfect harmony. As coffee drinker, I somewhat enjoy the coffee. Their coffee are not the best but still on enjoyable side. I ordered ice americano, the coffee is kind of light and a bit wateryeith notes on chocolate with bitter after taste. Not so much my liking but not so bad for coffee. Maybe next time, i will come back for milk based coffee. Pricewise, it is categorically expensive but it still worth it with taste and quality of the ingredients. The interior is also nice. It feels homey with many wood accents, the lighting is warm and romantic at night, the views are green and calming. Every thing is set properly, definitely  the best feature at buranchi. The last time, I went there it was brunch time and it was not that busy. The staff were helpful and quite attentive. There is nothing wrong the service, the order is spot on, didnt get too long to arrive on the table, the food is hot and tasty. Keep up the good service!

Dewasa itu ketika kamu sadar bahwa ramah bukan berarti merayu.  Perhatian bukan berarti cinta. Diam bukan berarti marah. Dan menangis bukan berarti lemah. Jadi sudah dewasakah kamu? Tapi ga perlu menjadi dewasa koq kalo cuma ke CL coffee & eatery, yang penting kalian bawa uang aja buat bayar makan dan minumannya. Menikmati segelas es kopi susu kamu, disitulah pertemuan pahitnya kopi berpadu dengan susu dan gula aren. Ditemani dengan bakwan jagung dan semangkuk chicken sambal matah yang enak dimakan selagi hangat, berbincang seru dengan bestie yang hanya ingin ngemil, ga makan berat setelah matahari tenggelam, diettt begitu alesannya. Jadilah mereka memesan beef dumpling dimsum dgn porsi 4 pcs, plattingnya estetik buat difoto loh. Area parkir kendaraan lega, pelayanan baik, harga terjangkau dan rame banged sama anak anak muda. Jadi merasa paling muda disana he-he-he...
review_translated_text: Adulthood is when you realize that friendly does not mean flirting. Attention does not mean love. Silence doesnt mean youre angry. And crying doesnt mean youre weak. So are you an adult? But you dont need to be an adult if you just go to CL coffee & eatery, the important thing is that you just bring money to pay for the food and drinks. Enjoy your glass of iced coffee with milk, thats where the bitterness of coffee meets milk and palm sugar. Accompanied by corn bakwan and a bowl of chicken with sambal matah which is delicious to eat while its warm, having a great chat with my bestie who just wants to snack, not eat heavily after the sun goes down, dieting is the reason. So they ordered beef dumpling dimsum with a portion of 4 pieces, the plating was aesthetically pleasing to take photos of. Spacious vehicle parking area, good service, affordable prices and very busy with young people. So I feel the youngest there he-he-he...

review_text: Pelayanannya cepat. Kopinya enak, recommended. French friesnya unik, ada topingnya mayonaise, dan mixed bawang bombay-ayam crumble-cabe yg dibumbu. Pisang gorengnya enak, pisangnya empuk, tepungnya krispi, rasanya kaya pisang goreng rumahan. Kurangnya cuma satu, kalo ambil tempat di bawah agak gerah. Gak tau ac nya lagi rusak atau emang sengaja diset gak terlalu dingin. Overall, suka dateng ke sini. Bakal dateng lagi sih kapan-kapan, tempatnya enak buat wfc atau sekedar ngobrol-ngobrol sambil ngopi. Tersedia buku-buku juga di raknya. Makin malem, makin banyak pelanggan yg dateng. Gak nanya ada musholla atau gak, tapi di deket situ ada masjid agak masuk ke dalem gang witana, masjidnya di sebelah kiri.
review_translated_text: The service is fast. The coffee is delicious, recommended. The French fries are unique, topped with mayonnaise, and mixed with spiced onions-chicken crumble-chilies. The fried bananas are delicious, the bananas are soft, the flour is crispy, it tastes like home-made fried bananas. Theres only one drawback, if you take a place downstairs its a bit hot. I dont know if the AC is broken or if it was deliberately set to not be too cold. Overall, I like coming here. Will come again sometime, good place for WFC or just chatting while drinking coffee. There are also books available on the shelves. The later it gets, the more customers come. I didnt ask if there was a prayer room or not, but nearby there is a mosque a little bit into the Witana alley, the mosque is on the left.

review_text: Sering lewatin tapi gak mampir2 pas rute alam sutera jadi penasaran dan ketagihan.. Bagi yg suka kuliner Iga (pork ribs) B2 wajib kesini ,dagingnya empuk banget recomend dah gak kalah sama Nur** diBali. Kesini 2hari berturut2 sampai dikenalin sm pelayan resto nih Pork bitesnya gak kalah rasa, enak, crispy anak2 pasti suka sih jadi perebutan. Pork ribs lebih enak cocol Sambal matahnya lope pull dah kalo gak pedas gak afdol, bisa kalap makan Ahog Pork Ribs sudah favorite keluarga apalagi sop bakutnya berasa manis,gurih gitu dan dagingnya moist sampai sikecil lahap makannya. Kalau dirumah masak bakut asem,gurih, asin ini berbeda rasanya kudu cobain yak Dipertahankan kualitas,,rasa & pelayananya yaa..
response_from_owner_text: Terima kasih Pak/Bu untuk kunjungan dan komentarnya untuk Warung Ahog Alam Sutera
review_translated_text: I often pass by but dont stop by on the Alam Sutera route so Im curious and addicted... For those who like B2 ribs (pork ribs), you must come here, the meat is really tender, I recommend it and its not inferior to Nur** in Bali. Came here 2 days in a row until I was introduced to the restaurant waiter The pork bites dont taste any less, theyre delicious, crispy, kids will definitely love them, so theyre worth fighting for. Pork ribs are better dipped in. The sambal matah is lope pull and if its not spicy its not afdol, you might go crazy eating Ahog Pork Ribs is already a family favorite, especially since the raw beef soup is so sweet, so delicious and the meat is so moist that your little one will eat it up. If you cook this tamarind, savory, salty bakut at home, the taste is different, you have to try it, OK? Quality, taste and service are maintained...
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you Sir/Maam for your visit and comments on Warung Ahog Alam Sutera

review_text: Baru tau ada cafe di Pamulang yg se-estetik ini, langsung melipir lah kita Suasananya adem, banyak tanaman, tersedia bangku di luar dan dalam ruangan serta di lantai atas. Ordernya harus ke kasir dulu, tunggu dan pick up sendiri orderan kita. Kerennya lagi sdh pakai alat alarm kaya di cafe2 Korea gitu. Untuk pilihan menu makanan dan minumannya cukup beragam mulai dari cemilan, makanan berat, roti /pastry, kopi, non kopi, dll. Saya pesan cinnamon roll dan ice hazelnut latte. Cinnamon rollnya cukup lembut dan rasa kayu manisnya tdk terlalu berlebihan, lebih enak kl dimakan selagi hangat yaa. Sedangkan tuk hazelnut latte kurang terasa hazelnutnya, jadi sangat disayangkan   Padahal pas saya tanya ke staffnya ada menu hazelnut latte. Tapi gpp masih bisa saya nikmati dan terbayarkan dgn penyajian yg estetik Kapan2 mau mampir lagi ahhh mau coba gelato dan menu lainnya
review_translated_text: Just found out that there is a cafe in Pamulang that is as aesthetic as this, we immediately covered it The atmosphere is cool, lots of plants, benches available outside and indoors as well as on the top floor. The order must go to the cashier first, wait and pick up our order yourself. Whats cool is that you use an alarm device like in Korean cafes. The food and drink menu choices are quite varied, ranging from snacks, heavy meals, bread/pastry, coffee, non-coffee, etc. I ordered a cinnamon roll and iced hazelnut latte. The cinnamon roll is quite soft and the cinnamon flavor is not too overwhelming, its better if you eat it while its warm. Meanwhile, the hazelnut latte doesnt taste like hazelnuts, so its a shame   Even though when I asked the staff there was a hazelnut latte on the menu. But it doesnt matter if I can still enjoy it and pay for it with an aesthetic presentation When do you want to stop by again, I want to try the gelato and other menus

review_text: Kelupaan foto yah temen2. Karena mampir kesini nyambi nunggu anak les. Kayaknya bakal balik kesini lagi. Klo pake mobil numpang di parkiran mitra10. Klo motor bisa langsung didepan cafenya. Baru masuk langsung pesan dan disambut pelayan yang ramah, karena beberapa cafe pelayannya standart Kemaren mesen makanan ramen, ini enak tapi mirip ramen instant rasanya dan tekstur mienya. Rasa enak tapi gak spesial tapi klo lg pengen boleh lah Mesen minuman redvelvet enak size juga lumayan banyak. Sama air mineral yang pake botol unik maaf agak katro hehehe Tapi sebenernya klo saya menilai cafe lebih ke suasana dan model kursi mejanya karena emank ke cafe buat ngegambar di tab dan klo salah posisi duduk bisa sakit leher, dan klo gak pakwe jg jadi gak bisa fokus. Dan cafe ini jd pilihan buat saya. Makanannya enak dilidah, banyak cemilan, sejuk, kursi mejanya pas nyaman. Dan penyusunan interior juga bikin nyaman terasa cozy banget
review_translated_text: Forgot to take a photo, friends. Because I stopped here to wait for my child to take lessons. Looks like Ill come back here again. If you use a car, take a ride in the Mitra10 parking lot. If you motorbike you can go straight in front of the cafe. Just walked in and ordered straight away and was greeted by a friendly waiter, because some cafes have standard waiters Yesterday I ordered ramen, it was delicious but similar to instant ramen in taste and noodle texture. Tastes good but nothing special, but if you want, thats fine There are quite a lot of delicious redvelvet drinks to order. Same with mineral water that uses a unique bottle, sorry its a bit confusing hehehe But actually, if I judge a cafe, its more about the atmosphere and the style of the table chairs because I often go to cafes to draw on tabs and if you sit in the wrong position it can hurt your neck, and if you dont use it you wont be able to focus. And this cafe was the choice for me. The food is delicious on the tongue, lots of snacks, cool, the table chairs are comfortable. And the arrangement of the interior also makes it feel really cozy

review_text: Kami satu keluarga datang saat malam hari. Tempat yang nyaman untuk makan kue dan pastry sambil ngopi. Sistem pelayanan yg tidak biasa, setelah pesan diberikan semacam alat yg berfungsi memberikan alarm apabila makanan sudah siap di ambil pada bagian pengambilan. Berikut scoring dari kami: Harga: 7 Makanan: 8 Tempat: 8 Kenyamanan: 9 Kebersihan: 7 Semoga sukses selalu. Kid-friendliness: Tersedia board games

review_text: Paul seemingly doesnt care so much any more. Came here for breakfast and got some disappointment the whole way. The service was ok, waiters a little slow but kind of friendly. But the food!!! 100k++ for a sandwich with dry, yes dry salad leaves and a thin like paper thin slice of tomato, which has seen better days two weeks ago. The bread hard like a cookie. They were lucky that we were starving. Otherwise, we would have left straight away. When we wanted to leave it took a good while for the waiters to realise. So in summary: The coffee was ok, so if someone wants to come for coffee and stay for hours without being bothered by a waiter, it might be a good place to go if you bring your own cleaning products to clean your table by yourself as the waiters didnt care much.

Overall service was good, the waitress was very supportive and kind, food was ok, relatively pricey but ok. I ordered spaghetti pesto with chicken breast, the chicken was yummy. Also ordered herbal tea and it was good. Special shout out to the waitress, we were staying till it closure time and asked help to take many pictures. And she was very patiently and happily assisting us (and the photo she took was also good, she told us which spot is better etc? Happy with the experience and will be back

review_text: Dont get me wrong by seeing the bad review. The service is good, the waitresses are really helpful. But the food is MAJOR disappointment. Seriously, make better food or just stick to pastry. Drinks are good. Pastry is good. Mushroom soup was INCREDIBLY salty. Im not exaggerating here, it was like eating salt with soup. Fortunately they apologized and took mine back and served another one which was ok. But it did not impress. Pasta did not impress. It was ok, but not the taste I was hoping for, for the price that I paid. I can find lots of other restaurants that serve way better pasta for that price level in BSD. Then came the Atlantic sandwich. It was DANGEROUSLY SALTY. I was not the only one who tasted and complained. We ate half, couldnt finish it, didnt want to risk our health. I paid the bill, which was 500k++, still hungry, disappointed, with a tinge of stinging saltiness in my mouth. We commented that food was not ok and was too salty, they mentioned that it came that way from the supplier. Well, do better! I cant believe youre THE paul le cafe from France. My dinner was ruined here. Seriously, FIX IT.

I like the croissants that I bought, it really taste like it was made with premium ingredients. It was 8 in the morning and they had only a few customers but it took some times to heat up my croissant. Other than that the staff and atmosphere was nice.

I recently visited Paul Bakery at The Breeze with my family for breakfast. After strolling around the area, we decided to stop by and try their offerings. We ordered a hot cappuccino, continental breakfast, a plain croissant, and a chocolate croffle. While the food was decent, it didnt particularly stand out or have any unique flavors. It was just okay, nothing remarkable. However, I must say that the service we received was excellent. The staff was attentive and friendly, ensuring we had a pleasant experience. Additionally, the ambiance of the bakery was lovely, creating a nice atmosphere to enjoy our meal. Overall, my visit to Paul Bakery at The Breeze was satisfactory. The food was average, but the outstanding service and pleasant ambiance made up for it

review_text: Found this little cafe/Kopitiam (ni he wo) on IG and decided to tried it. First floor is very minimal, more suitable for drinks and little snack stop only so we take 2nd floor which also have very little space about 7/8 table only. Food quality was great, especially the Laksa soup which was very flavourful although the beehon portion quite small. Soto also quite good along with nasi hainam, however the rice & chicken soy was quite dry. Ambience quite calm, but some guests which was a colleague/friends of the owner quite noisy despite all other guests tried their best not to make loud noise. The worst letdown was the slow service, it took almost 45 minutes for all three main course, really need improvement in this area. On first floor apparently they also make their own branded coffee of BLIV.

review_text: Kepada Yth Manager atau Owner Kopi Kenangan. Saya Hendra, Salah satu driver grab food yg kebetulan mendapat mendapat order dsini. Sebelumnya saya belum pernah mendapati perlakuan kasar Pelayan anda. Namun pagi saya merasa benar2 dikecewakan. Ceritanya begini, Awalnya saya bertanya tentang orderan saya, lalu dia menjawab antri. Ok, saya pun dengar dan mengerti. Lalu di belakang saya ada Driver Gojek bilang ke saya bahwa didepan order saya sudah jadi, saya lihatlah tu order, bukan punya saya karena jumlahnya 3, saya bilang ke driver itu bukan pnya saya. Eh, si pelayan dengan nada merendahkan ngomong  emang brpa sih pesenan lu, ? , Sontak saya kesel donk, saya lagi jawabin tmn gojek dibelakang bahwa itu bukan pnya saya malah di kata begitu. Oiya, karena saya kesel saya kasih aja tuh struk ke dia, ya orang kesel lah dilayanin marah2 dan dipancing2 emosi, malah ditambahin Ama dia  gw lemparin juga nih pesenan lu, . Sontak kedua x saya emosi dibilang begitu, berani bangt ngomong kek gtu didepan costumer, kita ini beli, saling menguntungkan, harusnya etika bicara dia tuh si pelayan yg bner lah. Di depan costumer lain Lho dia mau lempar orderan customer saya yg jumlahnya 1. Pembeli adalah segalanya. Tolong pihak resto tegur ni atau di training ulang.
review_translated_text: Dear Manager or Owner of Kopi Kenangan. Im Hendra, one of the Grab Food drivers who happened to get an order here. Previously, I have never encountered rude treatment from your waiter. But this morning I felt really let down. The story goes like this, At first I asked about my order, then he answered queue. OK, I heard and understand. Then behind me a Gojek driver told me that in front of me my order was ready, I looked at the order, it wasnt mine because the number was 3, I told the driver it wasnt mine. Eh, the waiter in a condescending tone said, How much did you order, really?, suddenly I was annoyed, I answered the Gojek friend behind me that it wasnt mine, but instead he said that. Oh yes, because I was annoyed, I just gave him the receipt, yes, the annoyed person was served by being angry and provoked by emotions, in fact Ama added, Ill throw in your order too,. Suddenly the second time I got emotional when I was told that, how dare I say something like that in front of a customer, we are buying, its mutually beneficial, the waiter should have the right speaking etiquette. In front of other customers, you know, he wanted to throw away my customers order, which was 1. Buyers are everything. Please reprimand this restaurant or retrain it.

review_text: Tidak memposting tentang keluarga, bukan berarti tidak sayang keluarga. Tidak memposting tentang pasangan, bukan berarti tidak sayang pasangan. Tidak memposting bersama teman, bukan berarti tidak punya teman. People easily judge us by our social media and too dumb to understand that feelings are more than just social media post. Entah kenapa sekarang aku juga merasa kalo posting sesuatu ke sosmed bukan lagi hal yg penting. Sesempatnya dan kalo pengen ajah hehehe. Hal yang terpenting sebenarnya adalah quality time kita bersama org org terdekat tanpa harus semua dishare ke sosmed. Seperti juga ditengah teriknya matahari bagiku penting sekali untuk mencari minuman pelepas dahaga. Fore coffee, hadehhh kenapa sih ini kopi enak parah. Tadi pesan kopi aren dan kopi pandan. Buat yang dirumah pesen dark chocolate dan matcha greentea. Oh ya tadi sempat ditawari kalo pake aplikasi untuk pelanggan pertama dpt diskon 50%. Tapi karna akunya pemalas jadi udahlah mba langsung pesen aja yak hehehe.... Minusnya cuma parkiran sempit cukup buat motor aja, tempat untuk duduk menunggu pesanan juga terbatas. Emang sih konsepnya take away. Tapi paling ga tambahinlah bangku buat kita nunggu pesenan ready.
review_translated_text: Not posting about family doesnt mean you dont love your family. Not posting about your partner doesnt mean you dont love your partner. Not posting with friends doesnt mean you dont have friends. People easily judge us by our social media and are too dumb to understand that feelings are more than just social media posts. For some reason, now I also feel that posting something on social media is no longer important. If you have time and if you want, thats fine hehehe. The most important thing is actually our quality time with the people closest to us without having to share everything on social media. Just like in the heat of the sun, it is very important for me to find a drink to quench my thirst. Fore coffee, hadehhh why is this coffee so delicious? I ordered sugar palm coffee and pandan coffee. For those at home, order dark chocolate and matcha green tea. Oh yes, I was offered a 50% discount if you use the application for first customers. But since Im lazy, Ill just order it straight away, hehehe... The only downside is that the parking area is narrow, just enough for a motorbike, and places to sit and wait for orders are also limited. Indeed, the concept is take away. But at least add a bench for us to wait for our orders to be ready.

review_text: Makan siang bersama suami dan anak. Tadi pesan Crispy Chicken Sambal Matah, Cumi Sambal Mercon, Spagetti Aglio Olio, Corn Ribs, Calamari, Honey Lemon, Matcha Latte, Irish Coffee sama Thai tea. Tapi, cumi sambal matahnya lupa dimasukin setelah ditanya, emang sih kasirnya nyebutin ulang pesenannya, akupun iya iya aja, karena aku kira sudah di masukkan semuanya. Setelah lama nunggu makanan suami gak dateng dateng, pas tanya, ternyata belum dimasukin. Yaudah langsung pesen aja ya kaaan. Miskom doang kok. Next time, harus lebih dengerin dengan seksama saat kasir ngulang pesenan. Untuk rasa makanannya, spagetti enak, al dente. Cuminya tadi kayaknya kebanyakan tomatnya dan tomatnya dipotong kegedean, but rasanya okay. Untuk crispy chicken sambal matah, oke banget sih, mantap. Corn ribsnya kayaknya kalau pakai saus pedes di jagungnya enak sih ya, mungkin nanti bisa jadi pilihan mau pedes atau enggak di cornnya langsung. Calamarinya okay sih ya. Honey lemonnya beneran seger banget, matcha lattenya juga enak pas, kalo thai tea nya standar rasanya. Terus untuk irish coffee nya rasanya kurang nampol sih. Yang bikin servicenya gak sempurna tuh, panggilan ke customer sih, aku di panggil tante. Prefer panggil ibu, atau kak aja gitu dibanding dipanggil tante. Huhuhuu Ples kalau bisa disiapkan korek ya, jadi kalo yang mau ngerokok lupa bawa korek, bisa pinjem. Thank you. *lupa fotoin menu dan suasanya yang asik banget*
review_translated_text: Lunch with husband and children. I ordered Crispy Chicken Sambal Matah, Squid Sambal Mercon, Spaghetti Aglio Olio, Corn Ribs, Calamari, Honey Lemon, Matcha Latte, Irish Coffee and Thai tea. However, I forgot to put the squid in the matah sauce after being asked, but the cashier repeated the order, so I said yes, because I thought everything had been put in. After waiting for a long time, my husbands food didnt come, when he asked, it turned out it hadnt been served yet. Well, just order it straight away, bro. Its just a miskom. Next time, you should listen more carefully when the cashier repeats your order. As for the taste of the food, the spaghetti is delicious, al dente. The squid seemed to have too many tomatoes and the tomatoes were cut too big, but the taste was okay. For crispy chicken with sambal matah, its really good, great. The corn ribs seem to be delicious if you use a spicy sauce on the corn, maybe later it will be a choice whether to add spicy sauce or not to the corn directly. The calamari is okay. The honey lemon is really fresh, the matcha latte is also delicious, the taste of Thai tea is standard. Then the Irish coffee doesnt taste good enough. What makes the service not perfect is that when I call a customer, Im called auntie. Prefer to be called mother, or just sis, rather than being called auntie. Huhuhuu Please prepare a lighter if you can, so if the person who wants to smoke forgets to bring a lighter, they can borrow one. Thank you. *forgot to take a photo of the menu and the really cool atmosphere*

Toilet tersedia didekat Owners Cafe, sebagai bagian dari kompleks apartment. Parking: Owners Cafe terletak di Gedung Apartment Brooklyn, Alam Sutera. Tempat Parkir Berbayae tersedia di lantai dasar (sejajar jalan umum) ataupun basement. Kid-friendliness: Ada Donut ataupun Cake yang aman untuk anak  anak, begitu juga menu lainnya.
review_translated_text: Order drinks for take away, service is fast, good and friendly. Payment can be made by Qris or other methods. The interior has a Doraemon nuance, certainly suitable for Doraemon lovers. The snacks are also quite delicious. There is also ice cream with various flavors. The Potato Donuts that we ordered are suitable for children. Likewise with the chocolate cake slice that we ordered. Toilets are available near the Owners Cafe, as part of the apartment complex. Parking: Owners Cafe is located in the Brooklyn Apartment Building, Alam Sutera. Berbayae Parking is available on the ground floor (parallel to the public road) or basement. Kid-friendliness: There are Donuts or Cakes which are safe for children, as well as other menus.

Makan yang porsi 3 potong juga sudah sangat membuat kenyang. Sayang waktu kesana nasi nya lagi gak ready, harus dimasak dulu kurang lebih 15an menit. Mungkin kurang cocok buat yang buru-buru ya tapi kalau untuk makan-makan santai, ngobrol atau wfc pas banget. Kakak staffnya helpful meskipun konsepnya self service. Plus, tempatnya bersih, cozy, ada wifi (banyak stopkontak!!) dan bisa pesan kopi juga. Keep it up~
review_translated_text: I came here during the office lunch break, happy that there is a new place to eat in the Alam Sutera Town Center area. Overall delicious! The wings are juicy, not dry and really big. Eating a portion of 3 pieces also makes you very full. Unfortunately when I went there the rice wasnt ready, it had to be cooked first for about 15 minutes. Maybe its not suitable for those in a hurry, but for a casual meal, chatting or WFC, its really suitable. The staff are helpful even though the concept is self service. Plus, the place is clean, cozy, there is wifi (lots of power outlets!!) and you can order coffee too. Keep it up~

review_text: Tidak semua tenant di dalam satu area food temptation menggunakan metode pembayaran kartu food temptation, dan juga sebaliknya, sehingga sangat membingungkan konsumen yang baru pertama kali datang, dan pada akhirnya kartu pembayaran tidak digunakan sama sekali karena beberapa tenant yang sangat ingin dikunjungi untuk dibeli makanannya menolak pembayaran menggunakan kartu food temptation yang sudah di top up sebelumnya. Konsep & kualitas tenant masih kalah jauh dibanding Futopia Alam Sutera yang dimana semua tenant di dalam satu area wajib menggunakan kartu pembayaran Futopia, sehingga orang yang pertama kali datangpun tidak langsung kebingungan.
review_translated_text: Not all tenants in one food temptation area use the food temptation card payment method, and vice versa, so it is very confusing for consumers who are coming for the first time, and in the end payment cards are not used at all because some tenants who really want to visit to buy food refuse Payment using a food temptation card that has been topped up previously. The concept & quality of tenants is still far less than Futopia Alam Sutera, where all tenants in one area are required to use Futopia payment cards, so that people who come for the first time are not immediately confused.

review_text: Tidak semua tenant di dalam satu area food temptation menggunakan metode pembayaran kartu food temptation, dan juga sebaliknya, sehingga sangat membingungkan konsumen yang baru pertama kali datang, dan pada akhirnya kartu pembayaran tidak digunakan sama sekali karena beberapa tenant yang sangat ingin dikunjungi untuk dibeli makanannya menolak pembayaran menggunakan kartu food temptation yang sudah di top up sebelumnya. Konsep & kualitas tenant masih kalah jauh dibanding Futopia Alam Sutera yang dimana semua tenant di dalam satu area wajib menggunakan kartu pembayaran Futopia, sehingga orang yang pertama kali datangpun tidak langsung kebingungan.
review_translated_text: Not all tenants in one food temptation area use the food temptation card payment method, and vice versa, so it is very confusing for consumers who are coming for the first time, and in the end payment cards are not used at all because some tenants who really want to visit to buy food refuse Payment using a food temptation card that has been topped up previously. The concept & quality of tenants is still far less than Futopia Alam Sutera, where all tenants in one area are required to use Futopia payment cards, so that people who come for the first time are not immediately confused.

review_text: PonJaa Food corner, is a new culinary destination that is now popping up in the Pondok Jagung area, Graha Raya, PonJaa is located on Pondok Jagung Timur street, which is a road passage from Alam Sutera, RawaKutuk to Graha Raya boulevard. This place is a food park with a wide variety of food stands, from steaks, noodles, dimsum, toast, snacks and angkringan, as well as juice and coffee. Very suitable for young people to hang out, can also be used as a place for reunions, social gatherings to small meetings. On the top floor there is also a spot for chatting with a big screen flat screen TV with a relaxed atmosphere. there is also live music every weekend. They have quite large space for car parking & motorcycle. For the taste, portion and price of the food, i think itsworth it. A little pity the food stand staff were busy chatting to themselves, not paying enough attention to the guests. Maybe also because it was not crowded enough that afternoon. Food 4/5 Service 4/5 Ambience 5/5

review_text: Tousta Signature Beef Bacon [brioche bread, red cheedar, scrambled eggs, beef bacon] . Rp. 32.000,- . The next level of toast!  @tousta.id betul2 step up their toast game sih, guys. Kali ini GoodDay cobain menu best sellernya mereka yg juga best in taste. Yang membedakan dari toast lainnya adalah @tousta.id menggunakan roti brioche, yakni roti yg biasa jadi pendamping pasta atau dijadiin garlic bread. Selain rotinya yg bikin special, scrambled eggsnya juga juara sih. Porsinya bener2 full dan lembut-wangi butternya terasa banget bahkan dari pertama kali toastnya dikasih ke kita, LOL. Dalam satu gigitan di menu ini kalian akan dapetin garingnya roti brioche, lembut dan creamynya scrambled eggs, smokynya beef bacon, dan gurihnya red cheedar  mantul! Dari segi porsi secara keseluruhan menurut GoodDay sih cukup ngenyangin ya, malah kayanya cocok untuk brunch nih. Recommended untuk kalian si toast hunter ----------------------------------------------------------------- Torikatsu Crispy Chicken [brioche bread, red cheedar, scrambled eggs, kaarage chicken] . Rp. 29.000,- . Yang ini juga ga kalah enaknya! Buat yg ngefans sama chicken katsu sih pilihnya menu yg ini ya. Di menu ini cukup balance ya antara tekstur crunchy dan lembut   crunchynya dari brioche bread yg dipanggang garing dan kaarage pieces nya, sedangkan creamy lembutnya dari buttery scrambled eggs dan red cheedar. Karena porsi scrambled eggsnya lebih mendominasi di menu ini, tekstur brioche di bagian bawahnya lebih cenderung lembut karena creamynya scrambled eggs (in a very good way ). Buat kalian yg biasanya suka celupin brioche bread saat makan soup, nah teksturnya sama nih kaya gitu. Garing di bagian atasnya, lembut di bagian bawahnya. So Good! . FYI, selain savory type toast, @tousta.id juga ada menu sweet toastnya juga loh. Varian camilan lainnya juga ada seperti cheesy fries, spicy chicken wings, hongkong style waffles dengan berbagai rasa yg ditawarkan. Yum!
review_translated_text: Tousta Signature Beef Bacon [brioche bread, red cheedar, scrambled eggs, beef bacon] . Rp. 32,000,- . The next level of toast!  @tousta.id really steps up their toast game, guys. This time GoodDay tried their best seller menu which is also the best in taste. What differentiates it from other toasts is that @tousta.id uses brioche bread, which is bread that is usually used as an accompaniment to pasta or made into garlic bread. Apart from the bread which makes it special, the scrambled eggs are also a winner. The portions were really full and soft - the aroma of the butter was really noticeable even from the first time the toast was given to us, LOL. In one bite on this menu you will get crunchy brioche bread, soft and creamy scrambled eggs, smoky beef bacon, and savory red cheedar  so delicious! In terms of overall portion, according to GoodDay, its quite filling, in fact it seems suitable for brunch. Recommended for you toast hunters -------------------------------------------------- --------------- Torikatsu Crispy Chicken [brioche bread, red cheedar, scrambled eggs, kaarage chicken] . Rp. 29,000,- . This one is no less delicious! For those of you who are fans of chicken katsu, choose this menu. This menu has quite a balance between crunchy and soft textures   the crunchiness comes from the crispy baked brioche bread and kaarage pieces, while the soft creaminess comes from the buttery scrambled eggs and red cheedar. Because the scrambled eggs portion dominates in this menu, the texture of the brioche at the bottom tends to be softer because of the creaminess of the scrambled eggs (in a very good way ). For those of you who usually like dipping brioche bread when eating soup, well, the texture is the same as that. Crispy on top, soft on the bottom. So Good! . FYI, apart from savory type toast, @tousta.id also has a sweet toast menu too. There are also other snack variants such as cheesy fries, spicy chicken wings, Hong Kong style waffles with various flavors on offer. Yum!

review_text: Dateng jam setengah 7 pagi kesini, nyobain sarapan disini udah lama dicilegon gak pernah nemu warung kopi kayak kopitiam di bangka, tempet nya khas kopitiam cukup besar dan bersih. Pesen kopi butter, kopi susu dengan butter terpisah sebenernya rasa nya enak cocok buat pagi hari cuma kopi nya gak panas pas dateng malah hangat jadi kurang enak ya minum kopi suhu nya gak pas. Terus pesen roti butter, ini roti nya di toast luar garing dalam nya masih lembut cocok banget ini roti temen sarapan pagi ditambah isian butter nya enak ada tambahan apa ya mungkin garlic jadi gak dominan manis ada rasa gurih dan aromatic, cuma kok pas dateng dingin ya kondisi rotinya padahal bekas ditoast kelihatan di luar roti nya. Terakhir pesen swekiau ayam masih temen nya dimsum, padet isiannya dan full terasa daging nya ditambah bumbu siramnya kerasa makanan cina melayu, overall menu disini enak cuma penyajian nya aja yang kurang pas menurut saya. Bakal balik lagi kesini sih buat nyobain menu lain dan ngopi pagi.
review_translated_text: Came here at half past 7 in the morning, tried breakfast here. Ive been in Cilegon for a long time and never found a coffee shop like Kopitiam in Bangka. The typical Kopitiam place is quite big and clean. Ordered butter coffee, milk coffee with separate butter actually tasted good, suitable for the morning, but the coffee wasnt hot when it arrived, it was even warm, so it wasnt delicious, so drinking the coffee wasnt the right temperature. Then order the butter bread, this bread is toasted, the outside is crispy, the inside is still soft, its really suitable for breakfast, plus the butter filling is delicious, what are the extras, maybe its garlic, so its not dominantly sweet, it has a savory and aromatic taste, but how come its cold when it arrives? the condition of the bread even though the toast marks are visible on the outside of the bread. Finally, I ordered chicken swekiau, which is still a friend of dim sum, the filling was dense and full of meat, plus the spices sprinkled with Chinese Malay food, overall the menu here was delicious, but the presentation was not quite right in my opinion. I will come back here again to try other menus and have morning coffee.

review_translated_text: You can really feel the Chinatown vibe at the Kranggan market in Jogja or Blok M. Even though you dont use AC, its not hot. awalnya penasaran bgt nih sama rasa bakmi disini, karena keliatan nya menarik. okelah lalu saya memutuskan makan siang disini. saya kesini jam 13.43, pesen 2 bakmi, kopi butter dan es jeruk.  es jeruk sama kopi dateng duluan, kopi butter nya oke, strong, rasa butter nya ketutupan. 30 menit berlalu, bakmi pesenan saya belum tiba juga. saya perhatikan pesenan meja sebelah juga belum dateng, padahal dia lebih duluan dari saya. gak lama, mas mas baju ijo dateng ke meja dan ngasi tau kita bahwa ada miskom sama kitchen. jadi kita harus nunggu 20 menit lagi untuk bakminy. kemungkinan karena ayam nya belum ready. entah ayam nya harus di oven atau di marinasi, katanya. terus mereka ngasi opsi mau nunggu atau di refund. wkwkw padahal udeh laper, tapi kita g bisa nunggu lebi lama lagi. meja sebelah kekeh untuk nunggu. saya minta refund. tamat. kalo udh cobain saya update
review_translated_text: At first I was really curious about the taste of the noodles here, because they looked interesting. okay then I decided to have lunch here. I came here at 13.43, ordered 2 noodles, butter coffee and orange ice. The orange ice and coffee came first, the butter coffee was okay, strong, the butter taste was covered. 30 minutes passed, the noodles I ordered had not arrived. I noticed that the next tables order hadnt arrived yet, even though he was earlier than me. Not long after, Mr. Green Clothes came to the table and told us that there was a problem with the kitchen. so we have to wait another 20 minutes for bakminy. Maybe because the chicken isnt ready yet. Either the chicken has to be in the oven or marinated, he said. then they gave me the option to wait or get a refund. Wow, even though Im already hungry, we cant wait any longer. the next table chuckled to wait. I ask for a refund. finished. If I try it, Ill update

review_text: Nyaman banget tempatnya. Pelayanannya ramah dan sigap, seneng banget walau bawa dua bocil, sama pegawainya dilayani dengan baik, ditungguin pesanan bocah dan dikasih rekomendasi yang enak enak. Ke sini pas buka puasa karena mau nyoba cromboloninya, ternyata dpt free takjil kolak pisang juga. Di sana nyoba beberapa menu juga, dari nasi goreng, mix platter, katsudon, dan chicken teriyaki, alhamdulillah g ada yang fail, bocil seneng banget, dan karena tersedia baby seat juga jdi enak ngafe walau bawa bayi. Minuman2nya juga enak, pesan vanilla latte dan matcha latteny juara. Kalau buat anak bisa pesen korean strawberry milknya. Ada mushola jga di lantai duanya, dn di lantai dua ada tmpat makan yng dekorasiny cantik banget. Pokoknya bakal balik lagi ke juffee Kid-friendliness: Ada menu yang pas buat anak2 kaya cemilan mix platter (sosis, kentang, mini siomay), kentang pompom, spaghetti, dll
review_translated_text: Very comfortable place. The service was friendly and alert, I was really happy even if I brought two children, the staff served them well, they waited for the childrens orders and were given delicious recommendations. Came here when breaking the fast because I wanted to try the cromboloni, it turned out I got free takjil banana compote too. There, I also tried several menus, from fried rice, mixed platter, katsudon, and chicken teriyaki, thank God none of them failed, my little one was really happy, and because baby seats were available it was also nice to hang out even if you brought a baby. The drinks are also delicious, order the vanilla latte and matcha latte. For children, you can order Korean strawberry milk. There is also a prayer room on the second floor, and on the second floor there is a place to eat which is really beautifully decorated. Anyway, I will come back to Juffee again Kid-friendliness: There is a menu that is suitable for children, such as mixed platter snacks (sausages, potatoes, mini dumplings), pompom potatoes, spaghetti, etc.

review_text: Suasana dan servisnya cukup baik. Sayang sekali makanan kurang enak. Tomyum seperti sup udang + cumi, rempah tidak terasa, jauh dari rasa tomyum. Ikan bakar ok, namun ukuran sangat kecil, kondimennya mengecewakan. Ayam teriyaki seperti ayam krispi kaki lima dengan tambahan saus teriyaki saja, kondimen failed, hanya miso sup yang ok. Fresh juice nya top lah. Kesimpulannya untun makanan dengan harga per orang 70-125k, not worth the price. Rasa kaki lima, harga bintang lima. Dengan harga segitu, bisa dapat makanan dengan taste yang lebih jos di luar hotel. Hanya bergantung ke ambience restoran saja yang di pinggir pantai.
review_translated_text: The atmosphere and service are quite good. Its a shame the food isnt delicious. Tomyum is like shrimp + squid soup, the spices are not felt, far from the taste of tomyum. The grilled fish is ok, but the size is very small, the conditions are disappointing. Teriyaki chicken is like crispy street chicken with the addition of teriyaki sauce only, the condiment failed, only the miso soup was ok. The fresh juice is top notch. In conclusion, food priced at 70-125k per person is not worth the price. Street food taste, five star prices. With that price, you can get food with a better taste outside the hotel. It only depends on the ambience of the restaurant on the beach.

review_translated_text: another my favorite Aceh noodles <3 in terms of food, this is really delicious. I highly recommend the stir-fried Acehnese noodles! There are normal, medium and spicy levels. For those who like spicy, the medium level is spicy and comfortable to eat. For those who dont like spicy, the medium level could be called spicy. on my tongue, the taste of the stir-fry soup has a curry + spicy taste from the noodle level + savory + eaten while its still warm  perfect! However, Im not used to the texture of the noodles because they are quite dough for me, who usually eats half-cooked noodles. On the positive side, the noodles are soft For cold Tarik tea, wow, the looks are very tempting, really tempting. especially when served by his brother. Regarding the taste of the tea, to be honest, Ive never tried the original, but its really delicious. the place is busy but comfortable, there are live music sessions with regional songs like that/? When you arrive, just tell us how many people, then my brother will tell you where to sit and you can order at our table. Payment can be made in qris. His brother is also kind, friendly (including small children), and also friendly.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you for your understanding and for our type of noodle product....it doesnt use preservatives...thats why it has a soft texture.....

Exquisite Chinese Cuisine with Exceptional Service at Restoran Central Serpong I recently had the pleasure of dining at Restoran Centrals Serpong branch, and the experience left me thoroughly impressed. This Chinese restaurant not only boasts a diverse menu but also delivers on taste with every dish, leaving no room for disappointment. Having harbored a long-standing interest in trying out Restoran Central Serpong, fueled by my previous satisfying experience at their Tomang branch in Jakarta, my expectations were high, and Im pleased to say they were exceeded. The culinary offerings span a variety of Chinese delicacies, each expertly crafted to perfection. From the first bite to the last, every dish on the menu is a flavorful journey that showcases the culinary expertise of the chefs at Restoran Central. Its safe to say that theyve mastered the art of Chinese cuisine. What sets Restoran Central apart is not just the delectable food but also the impeccable service that accompanies it. The staff exudes a level of professionalism that reflects the establishments commitment to excellence. The service is attentive, prompt, and truly elevates the overall dining experience. Its evident that the restaurant takes pride in offering a dining atmosphere that goes beyond just the food. While the prices may lean towards the higher side, they are undoubtedly justified by the exquisite flavors and top-notch service. Restoran Central Serpong doesnt just sell a meal; it sells an experience, and in this case, its an experience worth every penny. For those looking to host special events, Restoran Central Serpong provides a VIP room capable of accommodating around 100 guests. This feature adds another layer of versatility to the restaurant, making it an ideal choice for celebrations and gatherings. Conveniently, parking is available right in front of the restaurant, eliminating any hassle for patrons. The ease of access only adds to the overall positive impression I had during my visit. In conclusion, Restoran Central Serpong is a gem for Chinese cuisine enthusiasts. The combination of delectable dishes, impeccable service, and thoughtful amenities make it a dining destination worth considering, even with the relatively higher prices. If youre seeking an upscale Chinese dining experience in Serpong, Restoran Central should be at the top of your list.

Sisanya rasanya standard, tidak ada yang spesial bahkan ada yang tawar dan keasinan     kurang balance kasi bumbunya. . Rata-rata semua pasta yang dipesan oily banget, next better minta dikurangi biar ga becek di piring. Untuk gorengannya, masih oke dan sayuran di sandwich pun segar. . Rasa minumannya B aja tapi yang unik itu Pinky Mojito. Karena tempat minumannya besar banget kayak vas bunga dan rasanya asem manis segar plus bersoda.

review_translated_text: December is here, Christmas is just around the corner. Christmas is in the air! The Christmas decorations at Home Brew are really TOP. Reservations are mandatory if you want to hang out with your Bestie here. Even though it was busy, the service was quite fast. . Message: Potato Waffles Fries (Rp 45K) Beef Bolognese (Rp. 65K) Aglio Sambah Matah Smoked Salmon (Rp. 65K) Truffle Carbonara (Rp. 70K) Chicken Steak Sandwich (Rp 68K) Home Brew Fried Rice (Rp 55K) Lava Cake (Rp 40K) Lemon Poppyseed Cake (Rp 44K) Creamy Mushroom Soup with Truffle Oil (Rp 50K) Iced Cafe Latte (Rp. 35K) Iced Green Tea Latte (Rp. 37K) Iced Chocolate (Rp 42K) Iced Vanilla Latte (Rp. 40K) Pinky Mojito (Rp 42K) . Of all the orders above, I like the Lava Cake, Creamy Mushroom, Potato Waffles Fries and Aglio Sambal Matah Smoked Salmon the most. The rest tastes standard, nothing special, some are even bland and salty     theres not enough balance in the seasoning. . On average, all the pasta ordered is very oily, next time its better to ask for less so it doesnt get sludgy on the plate. As for the fries, theyre still okay and the vegetables in the sandwiches are fresh. . The taste of the drink is only B but what is unique is Pinky Mojito. Because the drink holder is really big, like a flower vase and the taste is fresh, sweet and sour plus fizzy.

Actually the ramen is delicious, I just asked for the spiciest level, its not spicy at all so the soup isnt delicious and the soup isnt tasty either. If you eat it when its not really hot, its a bit uncomfortable, but if its hot, its a bit helpful. It used to feel like the chili powder was provided, now its gone... the taste is really different from the old Gokana ramen. A bit disappointed with the taste now. The service also took a very long time even though it wasnt busy...

place_name: Gokana Ramen & Teppan - Summarecon Mall Serpong
review_text: Sebenarnya sudah lama ga makan GOKANA, akhirnya pas banget ada PROMO Merdeka selama bulan Agustus 2023. Pelayanannya lama sekitar 25 menit baru tiba di meja, sambil nunggu bisa ambil cemilan gratis. Suasananya biasa aja, lumayan rame pas malam minggu. . Ai cobain: Gokana 1 plus Ice Lemon Tea (Rp 47K) Satu paket dapet Nasi, Chicken Teriyaki, Mix Vegetables dan Fry Mix. Rasanya hambar, baik sayuran dan chicken teriyakinya. Cuman dipakaikan saos sambal saja, fry mixnya bisa ketolong hahahaa. Asli tawar! . Roasted Chicken Ramen Original (Rp 47K) Tekstur Ramennya over-cooked dan lembek. Kuahnya light, ga pekat dan hambar. Satu mangkok dapat tiga potong ayam panggang, irisan jamur, sayur dan setengah potong telor. Parahnya, tidak disediakan cabe bubuk gaes hahahaa. . Roasted Chicken Ramen Spicy (Rp 49K) Hampir sama dengan versi originalnya, bedanya di rasa pedes doang. Lumayan nusuk ke hidung, rasa pedesnya. . Es Teh Tawar (Rp 9K): No REFILL!
review_translated_text: Actually, its been a long time since Ive eaten GOKANA, so its finally fitting that there is a Merdeka PROMO during August 2023. The service takes about 25 minutes before arriving at the table, while you wait you can grab free snacks. The atmosphere is normal, quite busy on weekend nights. . Lets try: Gokana 1 plus Ice Lemon Tea (Rp. 47K) One package gets Rice, Chicken Teriyaki, Mix Vegetables and Fry Mix. It tastes bland, both the vegetables and the chicken teriyaki. Just use chili sauce, the fry mix will help hahahaa. Real bargain! . Roasted Chicken Ramen Original (Rp 47K) The ramens texture is over-cooked and soft. The sauce is light, not thick and tasteless. One bowl contains three pieces of grilled chicken, sliced mushrooms, vegetables and half an egg. Whats worse, theres no chili powder provided, guys hahahaa. . Roasted Chicken Ramen Spicy (Rp 49K) Almost the same as the original version, the only difference is the spicy taste. Its quite piercing to the nose, the spicy taste. . Fresh Iced Tea (Rp 9K): No REFILL!

review_text: [Review JUJUR] Udah berkali2 pesen delivery (dari tahun 2009) tapi, selaluuu aja saus pangsit gorengnya DIKIIIIIIT banget. Udah bilang ke mbaknya di telp buat saosnya banyakan tapi, selalu dikit dapetnya. Dari 10 pangsit paling saosnya cukup buat 4 pangsit goreng. Makanya jadi males pesen. Ini masalah kokinya ga tau porsiin saus atau mbaknya yg ga bilang? Kalau makan ditempat, parkirannya kecil banget. Lebih baik delivery atau via Gojek. Menu yang enak ada   bakmie ayam, pangsit goreng, nasi capcay, nasi tim( tambahin kecap asin) & Ifumie. Menu yang ZONK, ayam cah jamur. Karena beneran ga mirip sama GM. Ayam cah jamurnya kaya capcay dikasih ayam terus kasih kecap manis. Pangsit rebusnya juga ga halus seperti di GM. Nasgor biasa aja rasanya dan ga mirip GM. Saya perhatikan makin lama bukanya makin siang. Awal2 saya pesen jam 9:30 udah bisa pesen. Sekarang (2024) jam 11 baru bisa pesen ( ini bukan pas bulan puasa ya). Semoga kedepannya ownernya bener2 perhatiin dilapangan gimana kualitasnya dan makin baik deh. Apalagi GM udah buka d Living Plaza pamulang. Parking: Parkirannya kecil banget.
review_translated_text: [HONEST Review] Ive ordered delivery many times (since 2009) but, the fried dumpling sauce is always REALLY LIKELY. I told my sister on the phone to get a lot of sauce but always got a little. Of the 10 dumplings, the most sauce is enough for 4 fried dumplings. Thats why Im lazy to order. Is this a problem with the chef not knowing how to portion the sauce or the lady not telling him? If you eat there, the parking lot is very small. Better delivery or via Gojek. The delicious menu includes   chicken noodles, fried dumplings, capcay rice, team rice (add soy sauce) & Ifumie. The ZONK menu, chicken and mushrooms. Because it really doesnt look like GM. Chicken cah mushrooms are like capcay, given chicken and then added with sweet soy sauce. The boiled dumplings are also not smooth like at GM. Nasgor tastes just normal and doesnt resemble GM. I noticed that the later it was open, the later it became. I initially ordered at 9:30 and I was able to order. Now (2024) you can order at 11 oclock (this is not during the fasting month, right). Hopefully in the future the owner will really pay attention to the quality in the field and it will get better. Moreover, GM has opened Living Plaza Pamulang. Parking: The parking lot is very small.

review_text: Udah pesen delivery 3x selalu saus pangsit gorengnya kedikitan. Pesen 10 pangsit goreng, sausnya paling cukup buat 4. Udah berkali2 bilang ke mbaknya;  Mbak saos pangsitnya banyakan. review_text: Awful.. catastrophe !! Datang pas weekend, servernya cuma 2 orang, barista 1, servicenya slow banget, server nga attentive, kitchennya juga extremely slow dan quality of foodnya harus bener2 diperbaiki, oily bgt, ayamnya Keras, friesnya di cordon blue soggy bgt benyek. Kyk disiram pake minyak tuh piring. Order chicken cordon blue dan ayam kremes jam 19.34 baru di served jam 20.41. Liat servernya sampe kebingungan dgn orderannya harus diantar kemana, sampe nanya ke meja kita apa kita order nasi goreng dan kopi. Muter2 Nyari siapa yg order. Parah pokoknya catastrophe. Weekend Kan udah pasti rame. Teamnya kurang bgt. Management nya gmn nih..??!! Nyari person incharge nya nga keliatan. Entertainment keren tapi nga banget buat product and servicenya.
review_translated_text: Awful.. catastrophe!! Came on the weekend, there were only 2 servers, 1 barista, the service was really slow, the server wasnt attentive, the kitchen was also extremely slow and the quality of the food really had to be improved, it was really oily, the chicken was hard, the fries on the soggy blue cordon were really mushy. It looks like the plate has been doused with oil. Ordered chicken cordon blue and crispy chicken at 19.34 and only served at 20.41. When I saw the server, he was confused about where his order should be delivered, until he asked our table if we ordered fried rice and coffee. Playing around looking for who orders. Worse, its basically a catastrophe. Weekends are sure to be busy. The team is not very good. Whats the management like??!! Look for the person in charge, you cant see it. Cool entertainment but not really good for product and service.

review_text: Perlu bgt di evaluasi. Saya kesini 7 orang, malam minggu, jam 7an belum terlalu ramai. Untuk minuman oke lah dari segi kecepatan serta rasa. Tp untuk makanan, dari segi pelayanan dan rasa, agak mengecewakan. Pesan nasgor ayam 4, dateng hanya 2, udah gitu 1 kurang item telur, dan pikiran kita, yaudah paling lg ambil pesanan yg 2 lg dan sekalian antar telur. Ternyata engga, ini gatau emang kebetulan yang handle sedikit apa gimana, karena yg saya liat hanya ada 2 orang, dan ga ada atribut apron/kaos caffee. Saat komplain ke kasir, kasir tidak paham apa apam dan saat konfirmasi lagi me waitress yang mondar mandir ternyata dia bilang kurang 1 lg, yg mana harusnya 2,  dan belum dimasak nasgornya, jd nunggu lagi. Kerupuk yang digunakan sudah melempem dan ada juga yg kurang matang. Untuk Sayuran juga tolong di perhatikan kesegarannya. Lalu untuk onionnya terlalu tebal dan tepungnya sangat asin. Kondisi malming gini seharusnya banyak yg handle, tp yang mondar mandir hanya 2 orang saja, ini wajar bgt kenapa banyak terlihat juga pelanggan lain mengeluhkan hal yang sama. Sistem alarm juga kurang berguna kalo udah chaos begini. Tambahan saran, sendok garpu jangan letak dimeja jika tanpa alas, karena ujung sendok garpu terbuka, tisu hanya menutup bagian gagang saja, dan meja belum tentu bersih, apalagi outdoor. Dalam nota terdapat serv charge, harusnya ini jadi perhatian dan masukan.
review_translated_text: It really needs to be evaluated. I came here with 7 people, on a Saturday night, at 7 oclock it wasnt too busy. For drinks, its okay in terms of speed and taste. But for the food, in terms of service and taste, it was a bit disappointing. Ordered 4 chicken nasgor, only 2 arrived, thats it, 1 less egg item, and our thoughts were, well, at least take the second order and deliver the eggs at the same time. It turned out not, I dont know if it was a coincidence or not, because what I saw was only 2 people, and there were no cafe aprons/t-shirts. When I complained to the cashier, the cashier didnt understand what was wrong and when I confirmed again with the waitress who was pacing back and forth, it turned out she said I was missing 1 more, which should have been 2, and the nasgor hadnt been cooked yet, so I was waiting again. The crackers used were soggy and some were undercooked. For vegetables, please also pay attention to their freshness. Then the onion is too thick and the flour is very salty. There should be a lot of people handling a nighttime situation like this, but there are only 2 people going back and forth, this is very natural why you can see many other customers complaining about the same thing. The alarm system is also useless when its chaotic like this. Additional advice, dont put cutlery on the table if it doesnt have a base, because the ends of the cutlery are open, the tissue only covers the handle, and the table is not necessarily clean, especially outdoors. In the note there is a service charge, this should be a concern and input.

But I did have Problem with the Parking and those people who assist the Guests to Park. I couldnt get my Car out of the Parking Lot , because my car is quite Big and not enough space to move out since theres another car blocking the Entrance. I asked those people to call out for the owner of the car, so they can move the car. Therefore my Car could get out of it. But they insisted that theres enough space for my Car to got through. I was asked to drive my Car out through that small space. And my Nightmare came true. Its not enough for my Car to pass. It hit that other car that parked in front of the Exit gate. review_text: I can put my happiness and excitement in words when finding about this gem! I can safely say this is the most authentic local babi guling in the area. They nailed every components to the core, the infamous base genep. The pork broth, the pork satay that is beautifully seasoned with the base genep, and not to mention the lawar! Finally someone knows what lawar is (hint: its not urap with the long beans and coconut). Thrilled to know that I can eat babi guling that is freshly made, not some exported reheated frozen stuffs from Bali. A bit pricey and no air con, but for what you get, its definitely worth every penny. Will definitely find me here often

Bagi penyuka nasi campur babi khas Bali yang tidak suka rasa bumbunya terlalu strong/spicy, bisa cobain disini. Kebetulan selera saya cocok, karena kalau makan di beberapa resto bagul di Bali biasanya rasa rempah nya sangat kuat jadi berasa aroma seperti jamu. Nasi campurnya cukup lengkap, disajikan dengan rempah khas Bali, sayurnya di kukus kering kurang jelas sayur apa tapi dari teksturnya seperti sayur daun singkong. Topingnya kulit spicy babi dan krupuk kulit serta ada sate babi nya juga. Disajikan dengan side dish sup daging babi juga yang dominan rasa asin. Lokasi makan adalah ruko yang nyaman, bersih dan semi outdoor. Area parkir luas dan sampai saat review ini dibuat bebas parkir disana. Ambience musik gamelan dan ornamen khas Bali membuat acara makan semakin serasa di Bali. Recomended !
review_translated_text: For those who like Balinese mixed pork rice and dont like the taste of the spices being too strong/spicy, you can try it here. Coincidentally, my taste suits me, because when I eat at several Bagul restaurants in Bali, the spice taste is usually very strong, so it smells like herbal medicine. The mixed rice is quite complete, served with typical Balinese spices, the vegetables are dry steamed and its not clear what vegetables they are but the texture is like cassava leaves. The toppings are spicy pork skin and skin crackers and there is pork satay too. Served with a side dish of pork soup which also has a dominant salty taste. The dining location is a comfortable, clean and semi-outdoor shophouse. The parking area is large and until the time of this review, parking was free there. The ambience of gamelan music and Balinese ornaments makes the meal feel even more like being in Bali. Recommended!

review_text: Sebenarnya coffee shop ini bisa viral. Selama ini saya baru ketemu coffee shop dengan selera kopi Indonesia berikut jajanan pasar seperti roti jadul, siomay, bakso dan makanan tradisional Indonesia lainnya termasuk singkong ada semua di sana. Dengan dekor kafe yang sangat bagus dan nyaman karena ada AC dan bebas polusi udara termasuk asap rokok, bikin pengunjung penggemar kopi yang tidak merokok sangat betah, dan ini bisa menjadi faktor untuk menjual nuansa kafe dan menu untuk target market segmented penggemar kopi yang tidak merokok. Pelayanan harus lebih ditingkatkan, waiter di depan sudah sangat welcome untuk mengundang masuk pelanggan, tetapi sampai dalam terkesan tamu tidak begitu diperhatikan mungkin karena under staffed (padahal ketika kami masuk tidak begitu rame). Ada dua tingkat cafe nya, pengunjung bisa memilih untuk duduk di atas atau bawah sambil menikmati hidangan. Tetapi ketika kami datang, kami memilih lantai di lantai 1, itu pun agak susah untuk memanggil waiter, apalagi di lantai 2. Atmosphere dan makanannya sudah baik. Konsepnya bagus banget. Jika pelayanannya ditingkatkan semoga bisa jadi cafe yang rame di daerah Alam Sutera.
review_translated_text: Actually, this coffee shop can go viral. So far I have only come across a coffee shop with a taste for Indonesian coffee along with market snacks such as old school bread, dumplings, meatballs and other traditional Indonesian foods including cassava which are all there. With a cafe decor that is very nice and comfortable because it has air conditioning and is free from air pollution including cigarette smoke, it makes visitors who are coffee fans who dont smoke feel very at home, and this can be a factor in selling the feel of the cafe and menu to the target market segment of coffee fans who dont smoke. Service needs to be improved, the waiter at the front is very welcoming to invite customers in, but it seems that guests dont really pay attention, perhaps because they are under staffed (even though when we entered it wasnt very busy). There are two levels of the cafe, visitors can choose to sit upstairs or downstairs while enjoying a meal. But when we arrived, we chose the 1st floor, it was a bit difficult to call a waiter, especially on the 2nd floor. The atmosphere and food were good. The concept is really good. If the service is improved, hopefully it can become a busy cafe in the Alam Sutera area.
