review_text: Udah sering ke sini dari wfc, bawa anak dan meeting. Untuk minuman coffee nya cukup enak. Long black nya rasanya cukup body dengan nutty cuma after taste nya bitternya agak nyangkut tp tetep overall good coffee.. Untuk makanan, sebenernya dulu ada gyudon dan lumayan enak rasanya cuma terakhir ke sana sudah ga ada lagi. Onigiri.. ini highlightnya. Rasanya enak dan sangat puas makannya. Rasanya makan 1 aja ga cukup. Untuk harga so so, sesuai dengan kualitas yg di offer. Harga minuman sekitar 30-40an rb. Klo servicenya cukup cepet cuma kadang klo rame karena staff nya limited jadi lama tp ya tetep wajar aja. Kalau untuk staff nya karena sering ke sana sepertinya ramah semuanya. Keep up the good service ya!! Untuk suasana cukup japanese vibes, dan yang pasti parkir gratis!! Itu oke banget. Hehe Menurutku yang kurang sih cuma panas nya, karena dikelilingi kaca dan menghadap ke timur, jadi kalo pagi2, silau dan panas. AC nya yang banyak itu juga kalah. Cuma menjelang sore mulai berasa nyaman. Untuk nongkrong lama lama sih oke aja cuma harus tau posisi mana yang ga kena matahari langsung. Oiya, tempatnya juga cukup bersih, toiletnya agak jalan dikit tapi well maintained dan ada AC nya. Overall, it is good cafe. I can see the staffs are hardworking to improve the service, food and many many things. I hope u keep the good work!
review_translated_text: Ive been here often from WFC, bringing my children and meeting. The coffee drink is quite delicious. The long black tastes quite full of body and nutty, but the after taste is a bit bitter but still overall good coffee... As for food, actually there used to be gyudon and it was pretty good, but the last time I went there it wasnt there anymore. Onigiri.. this is the highlight. It tastes delicious and very satisfying to eat. It feels like eating just 1 isnt enough. The price is so so, according to the quality offered. Drink prices are around 30-40 thousand. The service is quite fast, but sometimes when its busy because the staff is limited, it takes a long time, but its still normal. As for the staff, because they often go there, everyone seems friendly. Keep up the good service okay!! For an atmosphere with quite Japanese vibes, and of course free parking!! Thats really okay. Haha In my opinion, the only thing lacking is the heat, because its surrounded by glass and faces east, so in the morning, its dazzling and hot. The many ACs are also inferior. Only in the afternoon did it start to feel comfortable. For hanging out for a long time, its okay, you just have to know which position is not exposed to direct sunlight. Oh yes, the place is also quite clean, the toilet is a bit of a walk but well maintained and there is air conditioning. Overall, its a good cafe. I can see the staffs are hardworking to improve the service, food and many many things. I hope u keep the good work!

review_text: Untuk sebuah cafe atau restoran, Boemboe Lawas memiliki makanan yg lmyn variatif. Namun, dari segi rasa sedikit over taste. Karena banyak makanan yang sedikit keasinan menurut saya. Dan, untuk varian tepung2an sepertinya satu tepung untuk semua ya? Karena cita rasa tepung n teksturnya sama. Padahal berbeda menu. Lalu, ada opsi untuk karaoke dan ada live music di hari tertentu di cafe tsb. Namun, untuk karaoke agak sedikit over menurut saya. Karena untuk ukuran luas dari restoran ini, bila semua bisa karaoke menurut saya agak over bising. Jd mgkn bs disiasati yg mau karaoke di ruangan VIP atau khusus. Kecuali live music. Karena bila live music itu adalah hiburan untuk semua. Namun, untuk karaoke adalah hiburan untuk yg bernyanyi dgn teman2nya yg dtg. Sehingga menurut saya agak sedikit mengganggu untuk tamu lain. Parking: Parkir di dalam area cafe hanya muat 3-5 mobil. Namun, bisa parkir di jalan ke arah perumahan.
review_translated_text: For a cafe or restaurant, Boemboe Lawas has quite varied food. However, in terms of taste, it is a little over tasted. Because many foods are a little salty in my opinion. And, for the various flour variants, it seems like one flour for all, right? Because the taste of flour and texture are the same. Even though the menu is different. Then, there is the option for karaoke and there is live music on certain days at the cafe. However, for karaoke its a bit over the top in my opinion. Because of the size of this restaurant, if everyone could do karaoke, in my opinion it would be a bit too noisy. So maybe you can get around this if you want to do karaoke in a VIP or special room. Except live music. Because live music is entertainment for all. However, karaoke is entertainment for those who sing with their friends who come. So in my opinion its a bit disturbing for other guests. Parking: Parking in the cafe area only fits 3-5 cars. However, you can park on the road towards the housing complex.

review_text: Hidden Cafe. 2 tahun tinggal di Pandeglang, sudah lihat dari kejauhan di jalan raya ada cafe, tapi beberapa kali ga nemuin masuknya dari mana. So, untuk teman-teman yang belum tau masuknya. Masuk aja ke Jl. Jend Sudirman Komp Pertokoan Cikupa, setelah lewat Dinas PU ada turunan curam sebelah kiri. Lurus saja lokasinya setelah jembatan kecil. Buka dari jam 2 pm - 11 pm. Kelebihan: - Minumannya enak-enak (Red Velvet Juara) - Tempat Cozy, waktu terbaik ke sini malam hari - Nyaman, bersih dan pelayanannya ramah-ramah Kekurangan: - Tidak  ramah pegawai kantoran nomaden sepeerti saya, yang suka nyari coffee shop untuk kerja. - No Wifi (Interaction only) --> kata tulisan di depan - Minim Stop contact
review_translated_text: Hidden Cafe. Living in Pandeglang for 2 years, I saw from a distance on the main road there was a cafe, but several times I couldnt find where it came from. So, for friends who dont know how to enter. Just enter Jl. Jend Sudirman Cikupa Shopping Complex, after passing the Public Works Department there is a steep descent on the left. Just go straight to the location after the small bridge. Open from 2 pm - 11 pm. Excess: - The drinks are delicious (Red Velvet Champion) - Cozy place, best time to come here is at night - Comfortable, clean and friendly service Lack: - Not friendly to nomadic office workers like me, who like to look for coffee shops to work. - No Wifi (Interaction only) --> the words written on the front - Minimal stop contact

review_text: An unique coffee shop with comfortable space and delicious coffees
A ways be my fave coffee shop at Pamulang.

Lokasinya berada di dalam Equestrian Pamulang. Untuk menunya yang tersedia disini standar seperti tempat kopi lainnya, ada espresso based seperti Latte atau Cappucino, ada juga drip seperti V60. Oh iya, sepertinya disini masih manual brew karena tadi saya tidak melihat ada mesin kopi. Harganya masih tergolong murah kisaran 15-30rb saja. Yang membuatnya unik adalah kita bisa memilih untuk duduk di rumput dengan menggunakan alas seperti tikar. Jadinya seperti sedang camping. Oh iya, di lokasi ini ada 2 anjing yang dibebaskan, meskipun anjingnya sudah jinak. Bagi teman teman muslim mungkin bisa jadi pertimbangan, but its fine. Mereka sudah biasa dengan banyak orang dan gak mengganggu kok. Oh! Karena lokasinya di Equestrian, tentu saja kalian bisa menikmati kopi sambil melihat kuda kuda yang sedang latihan.
review_translated_text: The location is inside Equestrian Pamulang. The menu available here is standard like other coffee places, there is espresso based like Latte or Cappuccino, there is also drip like V60. Oh yes, it seems like we still have manual brew here because I didnt see a coffee machine. The price is still relatively cheap, around 15-30 thousand. What makes it unique is that we can choose to sit on the grass using a mat like a mat. Its like camping. Oh yes, at this location there were 2 dogs that were released, even though the dogs were tame. For Muslim friends, this might be a consideration, but thats fine. They are used to lots of people and dont bother them. Oh! Because it is located at Equestrian, of course you can enjoy coffee while watching the horses being trained.

review_translated_text: Ive only been here twice, the concept is cool to be able to hang out while having your nails done... The drinks are refreshing and accompanied by cute cakes... But the brownies I got were just B... If you want to drink while having a pedi, cover the disposable packaging because Im afraid it will get dust in it when using it. machine for removing gel, so you cant see the color of the drink is a cool purple, its different from the menu photo. First time trying cat eye nail polish here, its really good, it lights up like that, it blinks following the light, the technique is also unique using magnets. Sis said the nail polish here is mixed by the owner himself, if there is a request for complicated nail art, for example for a wedding or drawings, it can be handled directly with the owner, as long as you make an appointment first. Its just that for me, the nail polish doesnt last for 2-3 weeks, darling... but its good

review_text: Menipedi disini udah yg ke 2x, dua2nya mengecewakan pdhal harganya gak murah. Pertama kali sakit pas dimenipedi, pikir mungkin pas dpt yg ga pengalaman, yg ke 2x sakit lg, sampai cantengan pdhal ga pernah sebelumnya. Pedicure kaki ga direndem, amplas kaki kyk ga di amplas masih bnyk kulit kasar tau2 udah ditinggal sama mba nya. Manicure tangan malah lecet n ngelupas2. Kerjainnya pdhal udah lama 2 jam tp masih ga proper
response_from_owner_text: Hallo kak, mohon maaf sebelumnya atas ketidaknyamanannya. Kami sangat menyayangkan kejadian tsb. Terimakasih juga atas keluhan yg telah disampaikan. Kedepannya akan kami perbaiki lagi. Apabila ada keluhan dan saran bisa hubungi ke no yg tertera di instagram ya kak agar kami bisa cepat perbaiki kerjanya. Trimakasih kak :)
review_translated_text: This is the second time Ive visited here, both times were disappointing even though the price wasnt cheap. The first time it hurt when I was put on a dipedi, I thought maybe it was something I didnt have experience with, the second time it hurt again, I got an ingrown toenail even though I never had it before. Pedicure didnt soak the feet, sanded the feet as if they werent sanded, there was still a lot of rough skin when I left it with my sister. Hand manicure ends up scratching and peeling. Even though its been working for 2 hours, its still not working properly
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hello sis, I apologize in advance for the inconvenience. We really regret this incident. Thank you also for the complaints that have been submitted. In the future we will improve it again. If you have complaints or suggestions, you can contact the number listed on Instagram, bro, so we can quickly fix the work. Thank you sis :)

review_text: Penasaran sama russian pedi nya. Hari pertama dateng ternyata ga bisa dikerjain krn yg bisa sedang ada customer. Disaranin booking via wa ato ig hari lain. Sudah booking via dm ig, buat besoknya jam 1 siang, 2 orang. Sudah bayar DP segala. Hari H dateng tepat waktu dan lagi2 harus nunggu. Point nya booking bukannya biar ga lama nunggu ya? Dr 2 orang yg ditanganin dlm 30menit cuma bisa 1. Akhirnya cancel yg 1 lagi, karena dibilang bakal nunggu 30menit lagi br bisa dikerjain. Luar biasa. Alasannya krn ada staf yg ga masuk. Kenapa ga dikabari sbl jam 1 kalo bgitu? Parah service nya. Ga semua org punya waktu luang banyak. Janji jam berapa ya tepatin dong. Thats why its called appointment. Alasannya gausa dikasi tau, itu masalah internal, harusnya cari solusi sendiri bukannya sibuk minta dimaklumi.
response_from_owner_text: Halo kak Evi Zhang. Kami mohon maaf sebesar2 nya atas kejadian yang terjadi. Hal ini terjadi dikarenakan salah satu staff kami mendadak berhalangan hadir dikarenakan ibunya sedang sakit. Semua jadwal appointment sudah kami jadwalkan dengan baik untuk menghindari penumpukan customer akan tetapi hal yang tidak terduga terjadi. Mengenai masalah tidak kami infokan sebelumnya dikarenakan kami sejak pagi sudah langsung pegang customer dan kejar waktu sehingga tidak sempat untuk mengabari. Di samping semua itu benar sekali ini adalah masalah internal kami, dan customer adalah yang terdepan bagi kami. Kami selalu berusaha mengutamakan kepuasan pelanggan meski terjadi hal hal yang tidak terduga. Kami segenap pihak Vuxia memohon maaf sebesar-besarnya.
review_translated_text: Im curious about the Russian pedi. The first day we arrived, it turned out we couldnt do it because there were customers who could. It is recommended to book via WA or IG another day. Have booked via DM IG, for the next day at 1 pm, 2 people. Ive paid all the down payment. The big day arrived on time and we had to wait again. The point of booking isnt so you dont have to wait long, right? Of the 2 people who were handled within 30 minutes, only 1 could be done. Finally, the other one was cancelled, because they said they would have to wait another 30 minutes before it could be done. Extraordinary. The reason is because there are staff who are not coming in. Why werent you informed before 1 oclock if thats the case? The service is terrible. Not everyone has a lot of free time. What time do you promise, please keep it. Thats why its called appointment. You cant tell the reason why, its an internal problem, you should find your own solution instead of being busy asking for an explanation.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hello Sis Evi Zhang. We apologize profusely for the incident that occurred. This happened because one of our staff was suddenly unable to attend because his mother was sick. We have scheduled all appointments well to avoid customer build-up, but unexpected things happen. We didnt inform you about the problem beforehand because we had been holding onto the customer since morning and were running out of time so we didnt have time to let them know. Apart from all that, it is absolutely true that this is our internal problem, and the customer is at the forefront for us. We always try to prioritize customer satisfaction even if unexpected things happen. We, the entire Vuxia party, apologize profusely.

review_text: I booked a Private Room, with a minimum charge of IDR 2 mio. My total spending was IDR 3 mio and received a very poor service here. 1. You guys spammed me with WA confirmations 3x on the D-day to ensure my arrival. 2. My expectation was high for Acta Gading Serpong, especially because the staff has been repeatedly sent WA message just to confirm my arrival. 3.My RSVP was at 4 pm, and I arrived early at the Private Room at 3.47 pm, but I still got a message on WA to confirm whether I would come to the restaurant or not! This means the staff isnt checking properly and constantly bombarding me with spam! 4. One of the main courses didnt come out for more than 1 hour. I called the waiters who were passing by in front of the Private Room, they all said yes but they didnt come immediately. Waiters handed over responsibilities to each other (ping-pong). Every time the waiter and waitress came, they were only answered okay, Ill check in the kitchen, BUT THEY DIDNT COME BACK to me again to update the status of the menu I ordered. 5. I had to go out from the private room again to look for the staff but I received a template answer from them I WILL CHECK TO THE KITCHEN ... BUT NO ONE CAME BACK TO ME to update the status of my order. I was really upset because I was left waiting for 1 hour for no clear answer! 6. I asked them to go back and checked PROPERLY in the kitchen and finally they came back to me for the status of my order and turned out that my order had not been COOKED / PREPARED IN THE KITCHEN.... after 1 hour!!!!!!!! 7. The customers in the resto were not that busy when we came, but the staffs still couldnt manage it. 8. This is not the first time I came to an expensive restaurant. However, the price I paid was not worth the experience I received. 9. My family and I will not return to Acta Gading Serpong again.

review_text: We reserved for 4 adults + 1 toddler but was initially brought to a square table fit for 4 (1 on each side) so we asked for a bigger table because it certainly cannot fit! Gave them: Five stars for ambience. Five stars for spacious parking lot. Five stars for services. Four stars for taste. Three stars for prices. So, Acta yang sebelumnya cuma ada cabang pusat di Senayan, sekarang buka di Tangerang, asik nih. Gading Serpong jadi punya opsi buat nongkrong cantik yang beneran proper, keren. Atmosphere nya asik ya. Cocok banget weekend vibes. Jujur dengan harganya, I expect so much more. Aku cobain: - pork belly arrabiata spaghetti (unik nih, cenderung mirip bolognese tapi lebih ringan, topping nya 3 pcs pork belly sedikit banget buat harganya hahaha) - salmon nori taco (good appetizers, boleh dicoba, bisa untuk sharing) - nasi campur bali (kaget karena even minta sambal matah/kuah balung nya sedikit saja dikenain charge, jadi males haha. Rasa oke enak, tapi ga stand out banget) - curry salted egg chips (make sure kalau pesan ini, kamu nya doyan curry ya. Curry nya lebih strong daripada salted egg nya. Garing renyah, enjoyable untuk sharing, karena rasa nya cukup heavy, tapi unik banget) Aku cobain flavor tea dan immune booster mereka, enak segar. Aku suggest kalau kesini malam ya. Lebih dapet gitu suasananya. Ada batas 2 jam ya untuk per kedatangan. Overall, kalau kamu cari vibes, boleh kesini. Juara deh. Tapi kalau cari makan kenyang, apalagi buat yang porsi makannya besar kayak aku, this place is not for you.
review_translated_text: Gave them: Five stars for ambience. Five stars for spacious parking lot. Five stars for service. Four stars for taste. Three stars for prices. So, Acta, which previously only had a central branch in Senayan, is now open in Tangerang, which is cool. Gading Serpong has an option for a beautiful hangout that is really proper and cool. The atmosphere is cool, isnt it? Very suitable for weekend vibes. Honestly with the price, I expected so much more. I tried: - pork belly arrabiata spaghetti (unique, it tends to be similar to bolognese but lighter, the topping for 3 pieces of pork belly is really small for the price hahaha) - salmon nori tacos (good appetizers, you can try them, you can share them) - Balinese mixed rice (I was surprised because I even asked for a small amount of sambal matah/balung sauce, so I was lazy haha. The taste was okay, but it didnt really stand out) - curry salted egg chips (make sure if you order this, you really like curry. The curry is stronger than the salted egg. Crispy, enjoyable for sharing, because the taste is quite heavy, but very unique) I tried their flavor tea and immune booster, delicious and fresh. I suggest you come here at night. Thats the atmosphere better. There is a 2 hour limit per arrival. Overall, if you are looking for vibes, you can come here. Champion. But if youre looking for a filling meal, especially for those who eat large portions like me, this place is not for you.

review_text: Pesan makanan : spaghetti pork belly arabiatta, nasi campur bali, peri peri chicken dan pandan lava cake untuk dessert. Spaghetti nya enak pedas dan babinya gak bau, peri2nya enak, smoky, gak pedas dan wangi. Yang kurang nasi campur bali krn terlalu dominan rasa minyak kelapa nya. Untuk dessert nya enak, rasanya masuk semua, sorbet kelapa nya juga seger cocok di makan sama kue nya. Servis nya bagus cepat dan makanan yang keluar juga gak lama nunggunya. Parkir gratis lahan parkir luas. Toilet bersih! Ada amenities nya seperti cotton buds, dental floss, softex, bahkan di sediakan mouthwash.
review_translated_text: Order food: spaghetti pork belly arabiatta, Balinese mixed rice, peri peri chicken and pandan lava cake for dessert. The spaghetti is deliciously spicy and the pork doesnt smell, the peri2 is delicious, smoky, not spicy and fragrant. Whats lacking is the Balinese mixed rice because the coconut oil taste is too dominant. As for dessert, its delicious, the flavors are all in, the coconut sorbet is also fresh, perfect to eat with the cake. The service was good, fast and the food came out and didnt take long to wait. Free parking, large parking area. Clean toilets! There are amenities such as cotton buds, dental floss, Softex, and even mouthwash is provided.

review_text: Acta Brasserie Gading Serpong memiliki ruangan outdoor dan indoor. Kalo outdoornya ga terlalu besar, dan agak panas,karena ga pake ac. Untuk indoornya lumayan luas. Untuk makanan, chicken cordon Bleu,ayamnya ga keras dan juicy, kentang gorengnya enak,saladnya biasa aja. Saus barbecuenya sedikit asin. Salted caramel macchiatonya rasanya biasa aja. Pelayanan cukup ramah. Hanya sayangnya kalo duduk di outdoor selain panas, ga ada staff yg standby di outdoor,sehingga kalo butuh sesuatu agak susah panggil staffnya.
review_translated_text: Acta Brasserie Gading Serpong has outdoor and indoor spaces. The outdoor area isnt too big, and its a bit hot, because it doesnt use air conditioning. The indoor area is quite spacious. For food, chicken cordon Bleu, the chicken is not tough and juicy, the fried potatoes are delicious, the salad is just ordinary. The barbecue sauce is a little salty. The salted caramel macchiato tastes just ordinary. Service is quite friendly. Its just a shame that if you sit outside, apart from the heat, there are no staff on standby outside, so if you need something its a bit difficult to call the staff.

review_text: Mengecewakan. Sebenarnya untuk rasa makanan not bad. Tapi untuk harga menu segitu, ekspektasi pastinya bukan hanya dr segi rasa saja tp juga service & ambience. Service di sini masih perlu banyak peningkatan & kebijakan2nya terlalu money oriented. Kita datang untuk merayakan ulang tahun papa ber8, karena acara ulang tahun, ada yg bawain puding & cake siomay. Kita juga ga ekspektasi untuk makan yg kita bawa di sana, tp kita mau tiup lilin & foto saja. Untuk titip kue/puding dr luar di kulkas resto akan dikenakan corkage fee Rp. 100k, kita pikir yasudah, ga dikulkaskan jg gpp ga akan rusak. Tp kita mau pinjam piring, untuk meletakkan pudingnya (karena puding yg dibeli di tempat lain ternyata tidak ada tatakannya), tapi ternyata ini jg dikenakan corkage fee  jujur agak kaget ya.. karena kita kan ga minta disajikan, dinyanyiin/dirayakan. Hanya sekedar mau tiup lilin Kita tanya emang di sini jual cake yg whole? Katanya ga ada, harus PO Karyawan blm paham betul tata cara service. 1. Waiter perlu ditraining ttg cara upselling & menjelaskan menu. Waktu ditanya apa yg paling direkomenasikan, disebutkan oleh waiter kami US prime porterhouse (menu paling mahal di menu) & dikatakan ini cocok utk sharing 4-5 orang. Sbg customer kita percayakan saja..ternyata waktu datang ini terlalu kecil utk jumlah org yg waiternya sebutkan & berat yg tercantum sudah berikut tulang. 2. Utk harga dgn range Acta brasserie, biasa kalau pesan still water setidaknya tuangan pertama akan dibantu tuangkan (yg lebih baik lg malah dituangkan terus setiap gelas kosong as this shows attentiveness)- di sini botol diletakkan saja di meja dengan gelas2nya. Padahal restoran sedang tidak penuh & banyak meja kosong. Not a big deal, but please take a note as this is such a basic service. 3. Waiter bolak balik mungkin niatnya mau bantu angkat piring kotor tapi seringkali yg memang kotor ditinggalkan, yg mau diangkat malah piring2 yg masih terpakai. Misalnya piring berisi salt pepper & lemon utk steak yg dipesan (steaknya masih ada & masih dimakan) mau diangkat juga    kok spt tidak tau menu makanan sendiri 4. Pesan teh panas, yg datang airnya kurang panas (cm hangat saja). Mau minta air panasnya diganti..tp ditanya: apa mau dihabiskan dulu aja yg di poci? Karena ketentuan di sini cm bs refill air panas 1 kali    pdhl dr awal air yg datang tdk panas kan bukan salah kita. Saran saya; tingkatkan servicenya kalau memang mau menjual menu dgn harga tsb & charge lebih utk service2 yg jujur saja menurut saya sepele & bisa didapatkan di tempat lain scr gratis bahkan tanpa diminta. Within the same price range, this is not the only place that sells decent food, there are plenty other places that serve delicious food whilst giving incredible service. If it were up to me, I won t be coming back here.
review_translated_text: Disappointing. Actually, the taste of the food is not bad. But for a menu price like that, expectations are definitely not only in terms of taste but also service & ambience. The service here still needs a lot of improvement & the policies are too money oriented. We came to celebrate our fathers 8th birthday, because it was a birthday event, someone brought pudding & siomay cake. We also dont expect to eat what we bring there, but we just want to blow out the candles and take photos. To leave cakes/puddings from outside in the restaurant refrigerator, you will be charged a corkage fee of Rp. 100k, we think thats it, dont refrigerate it and it wont spoil. But we wanted to borrow a plate to put the pudding on (because the pudding we bought elsewhere apparently didnt have a coaster), but it turned out that this was also subject to a corkage fee  Honestly, I was a bit surprised... because we didnt ask for it to be served, sung/celebrated. Just want to blow out the candles We asked, do we really sell whole cakes here? He said there wasnt any, it had to be PO Employees dont really understand the service procedures. 1. Waiters need to be trained on how to upsell & explain the menu. When asked what was most recommended, our waiter mentioned US prime porterhouse (the most expensive menu on the menu) & said it was suitable for sharing with 4-5 people. As customers, we can just trust it... it turned out that when it arrived it was too small for the number of people the waiter mentioned & the weight listed included bones. 2. For prices in the Acta brasserie range, usually if you order still water, at least you will be helped to pour the first pour (what is better is to pour it continuously every time the glass is empty as this shows attentiveness) - here the bottle is just placed on the table with the glasses. Even though the restaurant was not full & there were many empty tables. Not a big deal, but please take a note as this is such a basic service. 3. The waiter goes back and forth, perhaps with the intention of helping to lift dirty plates, but often the ones that are really dirty are left behind, the ones that want to be lifted are the plates that are still in use. For example, the plate containing salt pepper & lemon for the steak ordered (the steak is still there & still being eaten) I want to take it too    its like I dont know my own food menu 4. Order hot tea, the water that comes is not hot enough (just warm). I wanted to ask for the hot water to be replaced... but I was asked: do you want to just finish the one in the teapot first? Because of the provisions here, you can refill hot water once    even though from the start the water that came wasnt hot, it wasnt our fault. My advice; improve the service if you really want to sell the menu at that price & charge more for services which to be honest I think are trivial & can be obtained elsewhere for free without even being asked. Within the same price range, this is not the only place that sells decent food, there are plenty of other places that serve delicious food while giving incredible service. If it were up to me, I wont be coming back here.

review_text: I had the pleasure of visiting a small coffee shop located in one of the stores in the market, and I must say that it was quite an impressive experience. The shop is quite famous among the locals, and for a good reason. They use the best coffee beans from all over Indonesia, including Toraja, Aceh, Jayagiri, Mandailing, Bali, Temanggung, and even Arabica Luwak. Upon arrival, I was greeted with a warm and inviting atmosphere, and the aroma of freshly brewed coffee immediately hit me. The decor was minimalistic yet charming, with small tables and chairs arranged in a cozy setting. The staff was friendly and knowledgeable, ready to assist and offer recommendations. I ordered an ice latte with Arabica Gayo and a black coffee with Toraja coffee. Both were excellent, and I could taste the quality of the coffee beans used. The ice latte was smooth and creamy, with a perfect balance of sweetness and bitterness. The black coffee was robust and full-bodied, with a hint of smokiness. Although I didnt get the chance to try their assorted bites, Im definitely looking forward to it on my next visit. The coffee shop had a small selection of pastries and snacks, and I could tell that they were of high quality. Overall, I had a fantastic experience at this small coffee shop. The quality of the coffee and the friendly staff all contributed to a memorable visit. I highly recommend this coffee shop to anyone looking for a great cup of coffee in a warm and inviting setting.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for a good and kind review for us, thank you also for visiting our coffee shop. We look forward to your next visit.

Okelah jika kami hanya hanya numpang bermain saja, kami disini juga beli makan dan minum seperti pelanggan lain, dan keadaan foodcourt pun masih sepi, sungguh pengalaman yang tidak menyenangkan, karena baru kali ini di foodcourt kami bermain seperti ini, saya saja sampai tidak jadi memesan makanan lagi, padahal posisi lapar lagi, tapi apa boleh buat, sudah diusir ya kami pergi. Jika memang ada aturan yang melarang seperti itu, ya boleh silahkan ditempel dengan pengumuman atau apalah, kami menghormati aturan tersebut, tapi dengan posisi kami tidak mengganggu pelanggan lain dan bertransaksi di food court ini lalu ada orang yang seakan akan sebagai penanggung jawab alias mamang, sebagai pelanggan jujur saja saya dan teman teman tersinggung dan memutuskan untuk tidak kembali kesini lagi.
review_translated_text: Hmm, the first experience was not pleasant here, 5 friends and I came to play card games and eat and drink, then we were approached by someone who called himself mamang and said if you want to do this, you have to get permission from your mom or the one selling it which is strange , because we were just playing games while eating and drinking, then a few moments later this mamang came to throw us out by asking how long do you want to stay here?, which was rude in my opinion and my friends. Its okay if were just playing around, were also here buying food and drinks like other customers, and the food court is still quiet, its really an unpleasant experience, because this is the first time weve played at a food court like this, so I didnt even order. more food, even though I was hungry again, but what could I do, we had been kicked out so we left. If there is a rule that prohibits something like that, yes, please put it up with an announcement or whatever, we respect the rule, but in our position we dont disturb other customers and make transactions at this food court and there are people who seem to be in charge, aka mamang , as customers to be honest, my friends and I were offended and decided not to come back here again.
